47 // MachineLoweringReducer, formerly known as EffectControlLinearizer, lowers
48 // simplified operations to machine operations.
49 template <typename Next>
50 class MachineLoweringReducer : public Next {
51  public:
52  TURBOSHAFT_REDUCER_BOILERPLATE(MachineLowering)
53 
54  bool NeedsHeapObjectCheck(ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions input_assumptions) {
55  // TODO(nicohartmann@): Consider type information once we have that.
56  switch (input_assumptions) {
57  case ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone:
58  return true;
59  case ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kHeapObject:
60  case ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kBigInt:
61  return false;
62  }
63  }
64 
65  V<Word32> REDUCE(Word32SignHint)(V<Word32> input, Word32SignHintOp::Sign) {
66  // As far as Machine operations are concerned, Int32 and Uint32 are both
67  // Word32.
68  return input;
69  }
70 
71  V<Untagged> REDUCE(ChangeOrDeopt)(V<Untagged> input,
72  V<FrameState> frame_state,
73  ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind kind,
74  CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode,
75  const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
76  switch (kind) {
77  case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kUint32ToInt32: {
78  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Int32LessThan(V<Word32>::Cast(input), 0),
79  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision,
80  feedback);
81  return input;
82  }
83  case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kInt64ToInt32: {
84  V<Word64> i64_input = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
85  V<Word32> i32 = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(i64_input);
86  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
87  __ Word64Equal(__ ChangeInt32ToInt64(i32), i64_input), frame_state,
88  DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
89  return i32;
90  }
91  case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kInt64ToAdditiveSafeInteger: {
92  V<Word64> i64_input = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
93  // Check the value actually fits in AdditiveSafeInteger.
94  // (value - kMinAdditiveSafeInteger) >> 52 == 0.
95  V<Word32> check_is_zero =
96  __ Word64Equal(__ Word64ShiftRightArithmetic(
97  __ Word64Sub(i64_input, kMinAdditiveSafeInteger),
98  kAdditiveSafeIntegerBitLength),
99  0);
100  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check_is_zero, frame_state,
101  DeoptimizeReason::kNotAdditiveSafeInteger, feedback);
102  return i64_input;
103  }
104  case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kUint64ToInt32: {
105  V<Word64> i64_input = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
106  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
107  __ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(i64_input, static_cast<uint64_t>(kMaxInt)),
108  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
109  return __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(i64_input);
110  }
111  case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kUint64ToInt64: {
112  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
113  __ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(V<Word64>::Cast(input),
114  std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max()),
115  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
116  return input;
117  }
118  case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kFloat64ToInt32: {
119  V<Float64> f64_input = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
120  V<Word32> i32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(f64_input);
121  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
122  __ Float64Equal(__ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(i32), f64_input),
123  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN, feedback);
124 
125  if (minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
126  // Check if {value} is -0.
127  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(i32, 0))) {
128  // In case of 0, we need to check the high bits for the IEEE -0
129  // pattern.
130  V<Word32> check_negative =
131  __ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(f64_input), 0);
132  __ DeoptimizeIf(check_negative, frame_state,
133  DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
134  }
135  }
136 
137  return i32;
138  }
139  case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kFloat64ToUint32: {
140  V<Float64> f64_input = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
141  V<Word32> ui32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToUint32OverflowUndefined(f64_input);
142  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
143  __ Float64Equal(__ ChangeUint32ToFloat64(ui32), f64_input),
144  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN, feedback);
145 
146  if (minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
147  // Check if {value} is -0.
148  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(ui32, 0))) {
149  // In case of 0, we need to check the high bits for the IEEE -0
150  // pattern.
151  V<Word32> check_negative =
152  __ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(f64_input), 0);
153  __ DeoptimizeIf(check_negative, frame_state,
154  DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
155  }
156  }
157 
158  return ui32;
159  }
160  case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kFloat64ToAdditiveSafeInteger: {
161  V<Float64> f64_input = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
162  V<Word64> i64 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt64OverflowToMin(f64_input);
163  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
164  __ Float64Equal(__ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(i64), f64_input),
165  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN, feedback);
166 
167  if (minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
168  // Check if {value} is -0.
169  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word64Equal(i64, 0))) {
170  // In case of 0, we need to check the high bits for the IEEE -0
171  // pattern.
172  V<Word32> check_negative =
173  __ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(f64_input), 0);
174  __ DeoptimizeIf(check_negative, frame_state,
175  DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
176  }
177  }
178 
179  // Check the value actually fits in AdditiveSafeInteger.
180  // (value - kMinAdditiveSafeInteger) >> 52 == 0.
181  V<Word32> check_is_zero =
182  __ Word64Equal(__ Word64ShiftRightArithmetic(
183  __ Word64Sub(i64, kMinAdditiveSafeInteger),
184  kAdditiveSafeIntegerBitLength),
185  0);
186  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check_is_zero, frame_state,
187  DeoptimizeReason::kNotAdditiveSafeInteger, feedback);
188 
189  return i64;
190  }
191  case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kFloat64ToInt64: {
192  V<Float64> f64_input = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
193  V<Word64> i64 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt64OverflowToMin(f64_input);
194  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
195  __ Float64Equal(__ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(i64), f64_input),
196  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN, feedback);
197 
198  if (minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
199  // Check if {value} is -0.
200  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word64Equal(i64, 0))) {
201  // In case of 0, we need to check the high bits for the IEEE -0
202  // pattern.
203  V<Word32> check_negative =
204  __ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(f64_input), 0);
205  __ DeoptimizeIf(check_negative, frame_state,
206  DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
207  }
208  }
209 
210  return i64;
211  }
212  case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kFloat64NotHole: {
213  V<Float64> f64_input = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
214  // First check whether {value} is a NaN at all...
215  IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ Float64Equal(f64_input, f64_input))) {
216  // ...and only if {value} is a NaN, perform the expensive bit
217  // check. See http://crbug.com/v8/8264 for details.
218  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(f64_input),
219  kHoleNanUpper32),
220  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kHole, feedback);
221 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
222  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(f64_input),
223  kUndefinedNanUpper32),
224  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kHole, feedback);
225 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
226  }
227 
228  return input;
229  }
230  }
231  UNREACHABLE();
232  }
233 
234  V<None> REDUCE(DeoptimizeIf)(V<Word32> condition, V<FrameState> frame_state,
235  bool negated,
236  const DeoptimizeParameters* parameters) {
237  LABEL_BLOCK(no_change) {
238  return Next::ReduceDeoptimizeIf(condition, frame_state, negated,
239  parameters);
240  }
241  if (ShouldSkipOptimizationStep()) goto no_change;
242  // Block cloning only works for branches, but not for `DeoptimizeIf`. On the
243  // other hand, explicit control flow makes the overall pipeline and
244  // especially the register allocator slower. So we only switch a
245  // `DeoptiomizeIf` to a branch if it has a phi input, which indicates that
246  // block cloning could be helpful.
247  if (__ Get(condition).template Is<PhiOp>()) {
248  if (negated) {
249  IF_NOT (LIKELY(condition)) {
250  __ Deoptimize(frame_state, parameters);
251  }
252 
253  } else {
254  IF (UNLIKELY(condition)) {
255  __ Deoptimize(frame_state, parameters);
256  }
257  }
258  return V<None>::Invalid();
259  }
260  goto no_change;
261  }
262 
263  V<Word32> REDUCE(ObjectIs)(V<Object> input, ObjectIsOp::Kind kind,
264  ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions input_assumptions) {
265  switch (kind) {
266  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt:
267  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt64: {
268  DCHECK_IMPLIES(kind == ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt64, Is64());
269 
270  Label<Word32> done(this);
271 
272  if (input_assumptions != ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kBigInt) {
273  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
274  // Check for Smi.
275  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
276  }
277 
278  // Check for BigInt.
279  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
280  V<Word32> is_bigint_map =
281  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->bigint_map()));
282  GOTO_IF_NOT(is_bigint_map, done, 0);
283  }
284 
285  if (kind == ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt) {
286  GOTO(done, 1);
287  } else {
288  DCHECK_EQ(kind, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt64);
289  // We have to perform check for BigInt64 range.
290  V<Word32> bitfield = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
291  input, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntBitfield());
292  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(bitfield, 0), done, 1);
293 
294  // Length must be 1.
295  V<Word32> length_field =
296  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield, BigInt::LengthBits::kMask);
297  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(length_field,
298  uint32_t{1} << BigInt::LengthBits::kShift),
299  done, 0);
300 
301  // Check if it fits in 64 bit signed int.
302  V<Word64> lsd = __ template LoadField<Word64>(
303  input, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntLeastSignificantDigit64());
304  V<Word32> magnitude_check = __ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(
305  lsd, std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max());
306  GOTO_IF(magnitude_check, done, 1);
307 
308  // The BigInt probably doesn't fit into signed int64. The only
309  // exception is int64_t::min. We check for this.
310  V<Word32> sign =
311  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield, BigInt::SignBits::kMask);
312  V<Word32> sign_check = __ Word32Equal(sign, BigInt::SignBits::kMask);
313  GOTO_IF_NOT(sign_check, done, 0);
314 
315  V<Word32> min_check =
316  __ Word64Equal(lsd, std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min());
317  GOTO_IF(min_check, done, 1);
318 
319  GOTO(done, 0);
320  }
321 
322  BIND(done, result);
323  return result;
324  }
325  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kUndetectable:
326  if (DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector()) {
327  V<Word32> is_undefined = __ TaggedEqual(
328  input, __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_value()));
329  V<Word32> is_null =
330  __ TaggedEqual(input, __ HeapConstant(factory_->null_value()));
331  return __ Word32BitwiseOr(is_undefined, is_null);
332  }
333  [[fallthrough]];
334  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kCallable:
335  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kConstructor:
336  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kDetectableCallable:
337  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNonCallable:
338  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kReceiver:
339  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kReceiverOrNullOrUndefined: {
340  Label<Word32> done(this);
341 
342  // Check for Smi if necessary.
343  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
344  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ IsSmi(input)), done, 0);
345  }
346 
347 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
348  // Fast check for NullOrUndefined before loading the map, if helpful.
349  V<Word32> is_null_or_undefined;
350  if (kind == ObjectIsOp::Kind::kReceiverOrNullOrUndefined) {
351  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kFirstAllocatedRoot ==
352  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUndefinedValue);
353  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUndefinedValue +
354  sizeof(Undefined) ==
355  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue);
356  is_null_or_undefined = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
357  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(
358  __ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(V<HeapObject>::Cast(input))),
359  __ Word32Constant(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue));
360  }
361 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
362 
363  // Load bitfield from map.
364  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
365  V<Word32> bitfield =
366  __ template LoadField<Word32>(map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField());
367 
368  V<Word32> check;
369  switch (kind) {
370  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kCallable:
371  check =
372  __ Word32Equal(Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask,
373  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
374  bitfield, Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask));
375  break;
376  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kConstructor:
377  check = __ Word32Equal(
378  Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask,
379  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
380  Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask));
381  break;
382  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kDetectableCallable:
383  check = __ Word32Equal(
384  Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask,
385  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
386  bitfield, (Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask) |
387  (Map::Bits1::IsUndetectableBit::kMask)));
388  break;
389  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNonCallable:
390  check = __ Word32Equal(
391  0, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
392  Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask));
393  GOTO_IF_NOT(check, done, 0);
394  // Fallthrough into receiver check.
395  [[fallthrough]];
396  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kReceiver:
397  check = JSAnyIsNotPrimitiveHeapObject(input, map);
398  break;
399  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kReceiverOrNullOrUndefined: {
400 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
401  V<Word32> is_non_primitive =
402  JSAnyIsNotPrimitiveHeapObject(input, map);
403  check = __ Word32BitwiseOr(is_null_or_undefined, is_non_primitive);
404 #else
405  static_assert(LAST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE == ODDBALL_TYPE);
406  static_assert(LAST_TYPE == LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
407  // Rule out all primitives except oddballs (true, false, undefined,
408  // null).
409  V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
410  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(ODDBALL_TYPE, instance_type),
411  done, 0);
412 
413  // Rule out booleans.
414  check = __ Word32Equal(
415  0,
416  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->boolean_map())));
417 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
418  break;
419  }
420  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kUndetectable:
421  check = __ Word32Equal(
422  Map::Bits1::IsUndetectableBit::kMask,
423  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
424  Map::Bits1::IsUndetectableBit::kMask));
425  break;
426  default:
427  UNREACHABLE();
428  }
429  GOTO(done, check);
430 
431  BIND(done, result);
432  return result;
433  }
434  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSmi: {
435  // If we statically know that this is a heap object, it cannot be a Smi.
436  if (!NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
437  return __ Word32Constant(0);
438  }
439  return __ IsSmi(input);
440  }
441  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNumber: {
442  Label<Word32> done(this);
443 
444  // Check for Smi if necessary.
445  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
446  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 1);
447  }
448 
449  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
450  GOTO(done,
451  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())));
452 
453  BIND(done, result);
454  return result;
455  }
456  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNumberOrUndefined: {
457  Label<Word32> done(this);
458 
459  // Check for Smi if necessary.
460  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
461  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 1);
462  }
463 
464  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
465  GOTO_IF(
466  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
467  done, 1);
468  GOTO(done,
469  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_map())));
470 
471  BIND(done, result);
472  return result;
473  }
474  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNumberFitsInt32: {
475  Label<Word32> done(this);
476 
477  // Check for Smi if necessary.
478  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
479  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 1);
480  }
481 
482  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
483  GOTO_IF_NOT(
484  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
485  done, 0);
486 
487  GOTO(done,
488  __ Float64Is(__ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(input)),
489  NumericKind::kInt32));
490 
491  BIND(done, result);
492  return result;
493  }
494  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNumberOrBigInt: {
495  Label<Word32> done(this);
496  DCHECK_NE(input_assumptions, ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kBigInt);
497 
498  // Check for Smi if necessary.
499  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
500  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 1);
501  }
502 
503  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
504  GOTO_IF(
505  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
506  done, 1);
507  GOTO(done,
508  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->bigint_map())));
509 
510  BIND(done, result);
511  return result;
512  }
513 
514  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kStringOrOddball: {
515  Label<Word32> done(this);
516 
517  // Check for Smi if necessary.
518  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
519  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
520  }
521 
522  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
523  V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
524  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(instance_type, ODDBALL_TYPE), done, 1);
525 
526 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
527  GOTO(done,
528  __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
529  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map)),
530  __ Word32Constant(InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapUpperBound)));
531 #else
532  GOTO(done, __ Uint32LessThan(instance_type, FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE));
533 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
534 
535  BIND(done, result);
536  return result;
537  }
538 
539 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
540  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kString: {
541  Label<Word32> done(this);
542 
543  // Check for Smi if necessary.
544  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
545  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
546  }
547 
548  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
549  GOTO(done,
550  __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
551  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map)),
552  __ Word32Constant(InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapUpperBound)));
553 
554  BIND(done, result);
555  return result;
556  }
557  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSymbol: {
558  Label<Word32> done(this);
559 
560  // Check for Smi if necessary.
561  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
562  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
563  }
564 
565  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
566  GOTO(done,
567  __ Word32Equal(
568  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map)),
569  __ Word32Constant(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kSymbolMap)));
570 
571  BIND(done, result);
572  return result;
573  }
574 #else
575  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kString:
576  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSymbol:
577 #endif
578  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kArrayBufferView: {
579  Label<Word32> done(this);
580 
581  // Check for Smi if necessary.
582  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
583  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
584  }
585 
586  // Load instance type from map.
587  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
588  V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
589 
590  V<Word32> check;
591  switch (kind) {
592 #if !V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
593  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSymbol:
594  check = __ Word32Equal(instance_type, SYMBOL_TYPE);
595  break;
596  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kString:
597  check = __ Uint32LessThan(instance_type, FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE);
598  break;
599 #endif
600  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kArrayBufferView:
601  check = __ Uint32LessThan(
602  __ Word32Sub(instance_type, FIRST_JS_ARRAY_BUFFER_VIEW_TYPE),
603  LAST_JS_ARRAY_BUFFER_VIEW_TYPE -
604  FIRST_JS_ARRAY_BUFFER_VIEW_TYPE + 1);
605  break;
606  default:
607  UNREACHABLE();
608  }
609  GOTO(done, check);
610 
611  BIND(done, result);
612  return result;
613  }
614  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kInternalizedString: {
615  DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions, ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kHeapObject);
616  // Load instance type from map.
617  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
618  V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
619 
620  return __ Word32Equal(
621  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type,
622  (kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask)),
623  kInternalizedTag);
624  }
625  case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kStringOrStringWrapper: {
626  Label<Word32> done(this);
627 
628  // Check for Smi if necessary.
629  if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
630  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
631  }
632 
633  // Load instance type from map.
634  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
635  V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
636 
637  GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThan(instance_type, FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE), done,
638  1);
639  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(instance_type, JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE),
640  done, 0);
641 
642  V<Word32> bitfield2 = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
643  map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2());
644 
645  V<Word32> elements_kind =
646  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield2, Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask);
647 
648  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS
649  << Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift,
650  elements_kind),
651  done, 1);
652 
653  V<Word32> check =
654  __ Word32Equal(SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS
655  << Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift,
656  elements_kind);
657  GOTO(done, check);
658 
659  BIND(done, result);
660  return result;
661  }
662  }
663  UNREACHABLE();
664  }
665 
666  V<Word32> REDUCE(Float64Is)(V<Float64> value, NumericKind kind) {
667  switch (kind) {
668  case NumericKind::kFloat64Hole: {
669  Label<Word32> done(this);
670  // First check whether {value} is a NaN at all...
671  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ Float64Equal(value, value)), done, 0);
672  // ...and only if {value} is a NaN, perform the expensive bit
673  // check. See http://crbug.com/v8/8264 for details.
674  GOTO(done, __ Word32Equal(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value),
675  kHoleNanUpper32));
676  BIND(done, result);
677  return result;
678  }
679 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
680  case NumericKind::kFloat64Undefined: {
681  Label<Word32> done(this);
682  // First check whether {value} is a NaN at all...
683  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ Float64Equal(value, value)), done, 0);
684  // ...and only if {value} is a NaN, perform the expensive bit
685  // check. See http://crbug.com/v8/8264 for details.
686  GOTO(done, __ Word32Equal(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value),
687  kUndefinedNanUpper32));
688  BIND(done, result);
689  return result;
690  }
691 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
692  case NumericKind::kFinite: {
693  V<Float64> diff = __ Float64Sub(value, value);
694  return __ Float64Equal(diff, diff);
695  }
696  case NumericKind::kInteger: {
697  V<Float64> trunc = __ Float64RoundToZero(value);
698  V<Float64> diff = __ Float64Sub(value, trunc);
699  return __ Float64Equal(diff, 0.0);
700  }
701  case NumericKind::kSafeInteger: {
702  Label<Word32> done(this);
703  V<Float64> trunc = __ Float64RoundToZero(value);
704  V<Float64> diff = __ Float64Sub(value, trunc);
705  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64Equal(diff, 0), done, 0);
706  V<Word32> in_range =
707  __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(__ Float64Abs(trunc), kMaxSafeInteger);
708  GOTO(done, in_range);
709 
710  BIND(done, result);
711  return result;
712  }
713  case NumericKind::kInt32: {
714  Label<Word32> done(this);
715  V<Word32> v32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(value);
716  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64Equal(value, __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(v32)), done,
717  0);
718  IF (__ Word32Equal(v32, 0)) {
719  // Checking -0.
720  GOTO_IF(__ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value), 0), done,
721  0);
722  }
723  GOTO(done, 1);
724 
725  BIND(done, result);
726  return result;
727  }
728  case NumericKind::kSmi: {
729  Label<Word32> done(this);
730  V<Word32> v32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(value);
731  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64Equal(value, __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(v32)), done,
732  0);
733  IF (__ Word32Equal(v32, 0)) {
734  // Checking -0.
735  GOTO_IF(__ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value), 0), done,
736  0);
737  }
738 
739  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
740  GOTO(done, 1);
741  } else {
742  V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> add = __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(v32, v32);
743  V<Word32> overflow = __ template Projection<1>(add);
744  GOTO_IF(overflow, done, 0);
745  GOTO(done, 1);
746  }
747 
748  BIND(done, result);
749  return result;
750  }
751  case NumericKind::kMinusZero: {
752  if (Is64()) {
753  V<Word64> value64 = __ BitcastFloat64ToWord64(value);
754  return __ Word64Equal(value64, kMinusZeroBits);
755  } else {
756  Label<Word32> done(this);
757  V<Word32> value_lo = __ Float64ExtractLowWord32(value);
758  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(value_lo, kMinusZeroLoBits), done, 0);
759  V<Word32> value_hi = __ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value);
760  GOTO(done, __ Word32Equal(value_hi, kMinusZeroHiBits));
761 
762  BIND(done, result);
763  return result;
764  }
765  }
766  case NumericKind::kNaN: {
767  V<Word32> diff = __ Float64Equal(value, value);
768  return __ Word32Equal(diff, 0);
769  }
770  }
771 
772  UNREACHABLE();
773  }
774 
775  V<Word32> REDUCE(ObjectIsNumericValue)(V<Object> input, NumericKind kind,
776  FloatRepresentation input_rep) {
777  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, FloatRepresentation::Float64());
778  Label<Word32> done(this);
779 
780  switch (kind) {
781  case NumericKind::kFinite:
782  case NumericKind::kInteger:
783  case NumericKind::kSafeInteger:
784  case NumericKind::kInt32:
785  case NumericKind::kSmi:
786  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 1);
787  break;
788  case NumericKind::kMinusZero:
789  case NumericKind::kNaN:
790  GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
791  break;
792  case NumericKind::kFloat64Hole:
793 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
794  case NumericKind::kFloat64Undefined:
795 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
796  // ObjectIsFloat64Hole is not used, but can be implemented when needed.
797  UNREACHABLE();
798  }
799 
800  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
801  GOTO_IF_NOT(
802  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())), done,
803  0);
804 
805  V<Float64> value = __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(input));
806  GOTO(done, __ Float64Is(value, kind));
807 
808  BIND(done, result);
809  return result;
810  }
811 
812  V<Object> REDUCE(Convert)(V<Object> input, ConvertOp::Kind from,
813  ConvertOp::Kind to) {
814  switch (to) {
815  case ConvertOp::Kind::kNumber: {
816  if (from == ConvertOp::Kind::kPlainPrimitive) {
817  return __ CallBuiltin_PlainPrimitiveToNumber(
818  isolate_, V<PlainPrimitive>::Cast(input));
819  } else {
820  DCHECK_EQ(from, ConvertOp::Kind::kString);
821  return __ CallBuiltin_StringToNumber(isolate_,
822  V<String>::Cast(input));
823  }
824  }
825  case ConvertOp::Kind::kBoolean: {
826  DCHECK_EQ(from, ConvertOp::Kind::kObject);
827  return __ CallBuiltin_ToBoolean(isolate_, input);
828  }
829  case ConvertOp::Kind::kString: {
830  DCHECK_EQ(from, ConvertOp::Kind::kNumber);
831  return __ CallBuiltin_NumberToString(isolate_, V<Number>::Cast(input));
832  }
833  case ConvertOp::Kind::kSmi: {
834  DCHECK_EQ(from, ConvertOp::Kind::kNumberOrOddball);
835  Label<Smi> done(this);
836  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(input)), done, V<Smi>::Cast(input));
837 
838  V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
839  input, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
840  GOTO(done, __ TagSmi(__ ReversibleFloat64ToInt32(value)));
841 
842  BIND(done, result);
843  return result;
844  }
845  default:
846  UNREACHABLE();
847  }
848  }
849 
850  V<JSPrimitive> REDUCE(ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive)(
851  V<Untagged> input, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind kind,
852  RegisterRepresentation input_rep,
853  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation input_interpretation,
854  CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode) {
855  switch (kind) {
856  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kBigInt: {
857  DCHECK(Is64());
858  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
859  V<Word64> input_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
860  Label<BigInt> done(this);
861 
862  // BigInts with value 0 must be of size 0 (canonical form).
863  GOTO_IF(__ Word64Equal(input_w64, int64_t{0}), done,
864  AllocateBigInt(V<Word32>::Invalid(), V<Word64>::Invalid()));
865 
866  // The GOTO_IF above could have been changed to an unconditional GOTO,
867  // in which case we are now in unreachable code, so we can skip the
868  // following step and return.
869  if (input_interpretation ==
870  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned) {
871  // Shift sign bit into BigInt's sign bit position.
872  V<Word32> bitfield = __ Word32BitwiseOr(
873  BigInt::LengthBits::encode(1),
874  __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(__ Word64ShiftRightLogical(
875  input_w64,
876  static_cast<int32_t>(63 - BigInt::SignBits::kShift))));
877 
878  // We use (value XOR (value >> 63)) - (value >> 63) to compute the
879  // absolute value, in a branchless fashion.
880  V<Word64> sign_mask =
881  __ Word64ShiftRightArithmetic(input_w64, int32_t{63});
882  V<Word64> absolute_value = __ Word64Sub(
883  __ Word64BitwiseXor(input_w64, sign_mask), sign_mask);
884  GOTO(done, AllocateBigInt(bitfield, absolute_value));
885  } else {
886  DCHECK_EQ(
887  input_interpretation,
888  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kUnsigned);
889  const auto bitfield = BigInt::LengthBits::encode(1);
890  GOTO(done, AllocateBigInt(__ Word32Constant(bitfield), input_w64));
891  }
892 
893  BIND(done, result);
894  return result;
895  }
896  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber: {
897  if (input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32()) {
898  V<Word32> input_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(input);
899  if (input_interpretation ==
900  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned) {
901  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
902  return __ TagSmi(input_w32);
903  }
904  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
905 
906  Label<Number> done(this);
907  Label<> overflow(this);
908 
909  TagSmiOrOverflow(input_w32, &overflow, &done);
910 
911  if (BIND(overflow)) {
912  GOTO(done,
913  AllocateHeapNumber(__ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(input_w32)));
914  }
915 
916  BIND(done, result);
917  return result;
918  } else {
919  CHECK_EQ(
920  input_interpretation,
921  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kUnsigned);
922  Label<Number> done(this);
923 
924  GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(input_w32, Smi::kMaxValue), done,
925  __ TagSmi(input_w32));
926  GOTO(done, AllocateHeapNumber(__ ChangeUint32ToFloat64(input_w32)));
927 
928  BIND(done, result);
929  return result;
930  }
931  } else if (input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word64()) {
932  V<Word64> input_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
933  if (input_interpretation ==
934  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned) {
935  Label<Number> done(this);
936  Label<> outside_smi_range(this);
937 
938  V<Word32> v32 = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(input_w64);
939  V<Word64> v64 = __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(v32);
940  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word64Equal(v64, input_w64), outside_smi_range);
941 
942  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
943  GOTO(done, __ TagSmi(v32));
944  } else {
945  TagSmiOrOverflow(v32, &outside_smi_range, &done);
946  }
947 
948  if (BIND(outside_smi_range)) {
949  GOTO(done,
950  AllocateHeapNumber(__ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(input_w64)));
951  }
952 
953  BIND(done, result);
954  return result;
955  } else {
956  CHECK_EQ(
957  input_interpretation,
958  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kUnsigned);
959  Label<Number> done(this);
960 
961  GOTO_IF(__ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(input_w64, Smi::kMaxValue), done,
962  __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(input_w64)));
963  GOTO(done, AllocateHeapNumber(__ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(input_w64)));
964 
965  BIND(done, result);
966  return result;
967  }
968  } else {
969  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
970  V<Float64> input_f64 = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
971  Label<Number> done(this);
972  Label<> outside_smi_range(this);
973 
974  V<Word32> v32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(input_f64);
975  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64Equal(input_f64, __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(v32)),
976  outside_smi_range);
977 
978  if (minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
979  // In case of 0, we need to check the high bits for the IEEE -0
980  // pattern.
981  IF (__ Word32Equal(v32, 0)) {
982  GOTO_IF(
983  __ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(input_f64), 0),
984  outside_smi_range);
985  }
986  }
987 
988  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
989  GOTO(done, __ TagSmi(v32));
990  } else {
991  TagSmiOrOverflow(v32, &outside_smi_range, &done);
992  }
993 
994  if (BIND(outside_smi_range)) {
995  GOTO(done, AllocateHeapNumber(input_f64));
996  }
997 
998  BIND(done, result);
999  return result;
1000  }
1001  UNREACHABLE();
1002  break;
1003  }
1004  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kHeapNumber: {
1005  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
1006  DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation,
1007  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kDouble);
1008  return AllocateHeapNumber(V<Float64>::Cast(input));
1009  }
1010  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
1011  kHeapNumberOrUndefined: {
1012  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
1013  V<Float64> input_f64 = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
1014  DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation,
1015  any_of(ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
1016  kDoubleOrHole,
1017  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
1018  kDoubleOrUndefined,
1019  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
1020  kDoubleOrUndefinedOrHole));
1021  Label<Union<HeapNumber, Undefined>> done(this);
1022  Label<> allocate_heap_number(this);
1023 
1024  // First check whether {input} is a NaN at all...
1025  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Float64IsNaN(input_f64))) {
1026  // ...and only if {input} is a NaN, perform the expensive signaling
1027  // NaN bit check. See http://crbug.com/v8/8264 for details.
1028  bool need_hole_check = false, need_undefined_check = false;
1029  switch (input_interpretation) {
1030  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
1031  kDoubleOrHole:
1032  need_hole_check = true;
1033  break;
1034 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1035  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
1036  kDoubleOrUndefinedOrHole:
1037  need_hole_check = true;
1038  [[fallthrough]];
1039  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
1040  kDoubleOrUndefined:
1041  need_undefined_check = true;
1042  break;
1043 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1044  default:
1045  UNREACHABLE();
1046  }
1047 
1048  OptionalV<Word32> high_word;
1049  if (need_hole_check) {
1050  high_word = __ Float64ExtractHighWord32(input_f64);
1051  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(high_word.value(), kHoleNanUpper32), done,
1052  __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_value()));
1053  }
1054  if (need_undefined_check) {
1055 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1056  if (!high_word.has_value()) {
1057  high_word = __ Float64ExtractHighWord32(input_f64);
1058  }
1059  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(high_word.value(), kUndefinedNanUpper32),
1060  done, __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_value()));
1061 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1062  }
1063  }
1064  GOTO(done, AllocateHeapNumber(input_f64));
1065 
1066  BIND(done, result);
1067  return result;
1068  }
1069  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi: {
1070  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
1071  DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation,
1072  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned);
1073  return __ TagSmi(V<Word32>::Cast(input));
1074  }
1075  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kBoolean: {
1076  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
1077  DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation,
1078  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned);
1079  Label<Boolean> done(this);
1080 
1081  IF (V<Word32>::Cast(input)) {
1082  GOTO(done, __ HeapConstant(factory_->true_value()));
1083  } ELSE {
1084  GOTO(done, __ HeapConstant(factory_->false_value()));
1085  }
1086 
1087  BIND(done, result);
1088  return result;
1089  }
1090  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kString: {
1091  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
1092  V<Word32> input_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(input);
1093 
1094  switch (input_interpretation) {
1095  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kCharCode:
1096  return StringFromSingleCharCode(
1097  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(input_w32, 0xFFFF));
1098  case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
1099  kCodePoint: {
1100  return StringFromSingleCodePoint(input_w32, UnicodeEncoding::UTF32);
1101  }
1102  default:
1103  UNREACHABLE();
1104  }
1105  }
1106  }
1107 
1108  UNREACHABLE();
1109  }
1110 
1111  V<JSPrimitive> REDUCE(ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeopt)(
1112  V<Untagged> input, V<FrameState> frame_state,
1113  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind kind,
1114  RegisterRepresentation input_rep,
1115  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::InputInterpretation
1116  input_interpretation,
1117  const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
1118  DCHECK_EQ(kind,
1119  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi);
1120  if (input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32()) {
1121  V<Word32> input_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(input);
1122  if (input_interpretation ==
1123  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned) {
1124  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
1125  return __ TagSmi(input_w32);
1126  } else {
1127  V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> test =
1128  __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(input_w32, input_w32);
1129  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ template Projection<1>(test), frame_state,
1130  DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
1131  return __ BitcastWord32ToSmi(__ template Projection<0>(test));
1132  }
1133  } else {
1134  DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::
1135  InputInterpretation::kUnsigned);
1136  V<Word32> check = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(input_w32, Smi::kMaxValue);
1137  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision,
1138  feedback);
1139  return __ TagSmi(input_w32);
1140  }
1141  } else {
1142  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
1143  V<Word64> input_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
1144  if (input_interpretation ==
1145  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned) {
1146  V<Word32> i32 = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(input_w64);
1147  V<Word32> check = __ Word64Equal(__ ChangeInt32ToInt64(i32), input_w64);
1148  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision,
1149  feedback);
1150  if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
1151  return __ TagSmi(i32);
1152  } else {
1153  V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> test = __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(i32, i32);
1154  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ template Projection<1>(test), frame_state,
1155  DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
1156  return __ BitcastWord32ToSmi(__ template Projection<0>(test));
1157  }
1158  } else {
1159  DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::
1160  InputInterpretation::kUnsigned);
1161  V<Word32> check = __ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(
1162  input_w64, static_cast<uint64_t>(Smi::kMaxValue));
1163  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision,
1164  feedback);
1165  return __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(input_w64));
1166  }
1167  }
1168 
1169  UNREACHABLE();
1170  }
1171 
1172  V<Untagged> REDUCE(ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntagged)(
1173  V<JSPrimitive> object, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind kind,
1174  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions input_assumptions) {
1175  switch (kind) {
1176  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32:
1177  if (input_assumptions ==
1178  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kSmi) {
1179  return __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object));
1180  } else if (input_assumptions ==
1181  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::
1182  kNumberOrOddball) {
1183  Label<Word32> done(this);
1184 
1185  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1186  GOTO(done, __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1187  } ELSE {
1188  V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1189  object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1190  GOTO(done, __ ReversibleFloat64ToInt32(value));
1191  }
1192 
1193  BIND(done, result);
1194  return result;
1195  } else {
1196  DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::
1197  InputAssumptions::kPlainPrimitive);
1198  Label<Word32> done(this);
1199  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object)), done,
1200  __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1201  V<Number> number =
1202  __ ConvertPlainPrimitiveToNumber(V<PlainPrimitive>::Cast(object));
1203  GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(number), done,
1204  __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(number)));
1205  V<Float64> f64 = __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(number));
1206  GOTO(done, __ JSTruncateFloat64ToWord32(f64));
1207  BIND(done, result);
1208  return result;
1209  }
1210  UNREACHABLE();
1211  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kInt64:
1212  if (input_assumptions ==
1213  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kSmi) {
1214  return __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1215  } else {
1216  DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::
1217  InputAssumptions::kNumberOrOddball);
1218  Label<Word64> done(this);
1219 
1220  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1221  GOTO(done,
1222  __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1223  } ELSE {
1224  V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1225  object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1226  GOTO(done, __ ReversibleFloat64ToInt64(value));
1227  }
1228 
1229  BIND(done, result);
1230  return result;
1231  }
1232  UNREACHABLE();
1233  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kUint32: {
1234  DCHECK_EQ(
1235  input_assumptions,
1236  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kNumberOrOddball);
1237  Label<Word32> done(this);
1238 
1239  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1240  GOTO(done, __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1241  } ELSE {
1242  V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1243  object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1244  GOTO(done, __ ReversibleFloat64ToUint32(value));
1245  }
1246 
1247  BIND(done, result);
1248  return result;
1249  }
1250  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kBit:
1251  DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions,
1252  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kBoolean);
1253  return __ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(factory_->true_value()));
1254  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kFloat64: {
1255  if (input_assumptions == ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::
1256  InputAssumptions::kNumberOrOddball) {
1257  Label<Float64> done(this);
1258 
1259  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1260  GOTO(done,
1261  __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1262  } ELSE {
1263  V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1264  object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1265  GOTO(done, value);
1266  }
1267 
1268  BIND(done, result);
1269  return result;
1270  } else {
1271  DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::
1272  InputAssumptions::kPlainPrimitive);
1273  Label<Float64> done(this);
1274  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object)), done,
1275  __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1276  V<Number> number =
1277  __ ConvertPlainPrimitiveToNumber(V<PlainPrimitive>::Cast(object));
1278  GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(number), done,
1279  __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(number))));
1280  V<Float64> f64 = __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(number));
1281  GOTO(done, f64);
1282  BIND(done, result);
1283  return result;
1284  }
1285  }
1286 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1287  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kHoleyFloat64: {
1288  DCHECK_EQ(
1289  input_assumptions,
1290  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kNumberOrOddball);
1291  Label<Float64> done(this);
1292 
1293  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1294  GOTO(done,
1295  __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1296  } ELSE {
1297  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(V<HeapObject>::Cast(object));
1298  GOTO_IF(
1299  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_map())),
1300  done, UndefinedNan());
1301  IF (UNLIKELY(
1302  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->hole_map())))) {
1303  __ Unreachable();
1304  }
1305 
1306  V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1307  object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1308  V<Float64> silenced_value = __ Float64SilenceNaN(value);
1309  GOTO(done, silenced_value);
1310  }
1311 
1312  BIND(done, result);
1313  return result;
1314  }
1315 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1316  }
1317  UNREACHABLE();
1318  }
1319 
1320  V<Untagged> REDUCE(ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeopt)(
1321  V<Object> object, V<FrameState> frame_state,
1322  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind from_kind,
1323  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind to_kind,
1324  CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode, const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
1325  switch (to_kind) {
1326  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32: {
1327  if (from_kind ==
1328  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi) {
1329  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ ObjectIsSmi(object), frame_state,
1330  DeoptimizeReason::kNotASmi, feedback);
1331  return __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object));
1332  } else {
1333  DCHECK_EQ(
1334  from_kind,
1335  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber);
1336  Label<Word32> done(this);
1337 
1338  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1339  GOTO(done, __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1340  } ELSE {
1341  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
1342  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
1343  __ TaggedEqual(map,
1344  __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
1345  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber, feedback);
1346  V<Float64> heap_number_value =
1347  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(object));
1348 
1349  GOTO(done,
1350  __ ChangeFloat64ToInt32OrDeopt(heap_number_value, frame_state,
1351  minus_zero_mode, feedback));
1352  }
1353 
1354  BIND(done, result);
1355  return result;
1356  }
1357  }
1358  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::
1359  kAdditiveSafeInteger: {
1360  DCHECK_EQ(
1361  from_kind,
1362  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber);
1363  Label<Word64> done(this);
1364 
1365  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1366  GOTO(done, __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1367  } ELSE {
1368  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
1369  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
1370  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
1371  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber, feedback);
1372  V<Float64> heap_number_value =
1373  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(object));
1374  GOTO(done,
1375  __ ChangeFloat64ToAdditiveSafeIntegerOrDeopt(
1376  heap_number_value, frame_state, minus_zero_mode, feedback));
1377  }
1378 
1379  BIND(done, result);
1380  return result;
1381  }
1382  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kInt64: {
1383  DCHECK_EQ(
1384  from_kind,
1385  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber);
1386  Label<Word64> done(this);
1387 
1388  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1389  GOTO(done, __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1390  } ELSE {
1391  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
1392  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
1393  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
1394  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber, feedback);
1395  V<Float64> heap_number_value =
1396  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(object));
1397  GOTO(done,
1398  __ ChangeFloat64ToInt64OrDeopt(heap_number_value, frame_state,
1399  minus_zero_mode, feedback));
1400  }
1401 
1402  BIND(done, result);
1403  return result;
1404  }
1405  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kFloat64: {
1406  Label<Float64> done(this);
1407 
1408  // In the Smi case, just convert to int32 and then float64.
1409  // Otherwise, check heap numberness and load the number.
1410  IF (__ ObjectIsSmi(object)) {
1411  GOTO(done,
1412  __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1413  } ELSE {
1414  GOTO(done, ConvertHeapObjectToFloat64OrDeopt(object, frame_state,
1415  from_kind, feedback));
1416  }
1417 
1418  BIND(done, result);
1419  return result;
1420  }
1421 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1422  // TODO(nicohartmann): Consider merging this into
1423  // ConvertHeapObjectToFloat64OrDeopt.
1424  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kHoleyFloat64: {
1425  DCHECK_EQ(from_kind, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::
1426  JSPrimitiveKind::kNumberOrOddball);
1427  Label<Float64> done(this);
1428 
1429  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1430  GOTO(done,
1431  __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1432  } ELSE {
1433  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(V<HeapObject>::Cast(object));
1434  GOTO_IF(
1435  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_map())),
1436  done, UndefinedNan());
1437  IF (UNLIKELY(
1438  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->hole_map())))) {
1439  __ Unreachable();
1440  }
1441 
1442  V<Float64> value = ConvertHeapObjectToFloat64OrDeopt(
1443  object, frame_state, from_kind, feedback, map);
1444  V<Float64> silenced_value = __ Float64SilenceNaN(value);
1445  GOTO(done, silenced_value);
1446  }
1447 
1448  BIND(done, result);
1449  return result;
1450  }
1451 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1452 
1453  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kArrayIndex: {
1454  DCHECK_EQ(from_kind, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::
1455  JSPrimitiveKind::kNumberOrString);
1456  Label<WordPtr> done(this);
1457 
1458  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1459  // In the Smi case, just convert to intptr_t.
1460  GOTO(done, __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1461  } ELSE {
1462  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
1463  IF (LIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
1464  map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())))) {
1465  V<Float64> heap_number_value =
1466  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(object));
1467  // Perform Turbofan's "CheckedFloat64ToIndex"
1468  {
1469  if constexpr (Is64()) {
1470  V<Word64> i64 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt64OverflowUndefined(
1471  heap_number_value);
1472  // The TruncateKind above means there will be a precision loss
1473  // in case INT64_MAX input is passed, but that precision loss
1474  // would not be detected and would not lead to a deoptimization
1475  // from the first check. But in this case, we'll deopt anyway
1476  // because of the following checks.
1477  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ Float64Equal(__ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(i64),
1478  heap_number_value),
1479  frame_state,
1480  DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN,
1481  feedback);
1482  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
1483  __ IntPtrLessThan(i64, kMaxSafeIntegerUint64), frame_state,
1484  DeoptimizeReason::kNotAnArrayIndex, feedback);
1485  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
1486  __ IntPtrLessThan(-kMaxSafeIntegerUint64, i64), frame_state,
1487  DeoptimizeReason::kNotAnArrayIndex, feedback);
1488  GOTO(done, i64);
1489  } else {
1490  V<Word32> i32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(
1491  heap_number_value);
1492  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ Float64Equal(__ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(i32),
1493  heap_number_value),
1494  frame_state,
1495  DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN,
1496  feedback);
1497  GOTO(done, i32);
1498  }
1499  }
1500  } ELSE {
1501 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
1502  V<Word32> is_string_map = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
1503  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map)),
1504  __ Word32Constant(InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapUpperBound));
1505 #else
1506  V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
1507  V<Word32> is_string_map =
1508  __ Uint32LessThan(instance_type, FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE);
1509 #endif
1510  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(is_string_map, frame_state,
1511  DeoptimizeReason::kNotAString, feedback);
1512 
1513  // TODO(nicohartmann@): We might introduce a Turboshaft way for
1514  // constructing call descriptors.
1515  MachineSignature::Builder builder(__ graph_zone(), 1, 1);
1516  builder.AddReturn(MachineType::Int32());
1517  builder.AddParam(MachineType::TaggedPointer());
1518  auto desc = Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(__ graph_zone(),
1519  builder.Get());
1520  auto ts_desc = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
1521  desc, CanThrow::kNo, LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo, __ graph_zone());
1522  OpIndex callee = __ ExternalConstant(
1523  ExternalReference::string_to_array_index_function());
1524  // NOTE: String::ToArrayIndex() currently returns int32_t.
1525  V<WordPtr> index = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(
1526  V<Word32>::Cast(__ Call(callee, {object}, ts_desc)));
1527  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ WordPtrEqual(index, -1), frame_state,
1528  DeoptimizeReason::kNotAnArrayIndex, feedback);
1529  GOTO(done, index);
1530  }
1531  }
1532 
1533  BIND(done, result);
1534  return result;
1535  }
1536  }
1537  UNREACHABLE();
1538  }
1539 
1540  V<Word> REDUCE(TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntagged)(
1541  V<JSPrimitive> object, TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind kind,
1542  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions input_assumptions) {
1543  switch (kind) {
1544  case TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32: {
1545  DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions, TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::
1546  InputAssumptions::kNumberOrOddball);
1547  Label<Word32> done(this);
1548 
1549  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1550  GOTO(done, __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1551  } ELSE {
1552  V<Float64> number_value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1553  object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1554  GOTO(done, __ JSTruncateFloat64ToWord32(number_value));
1555  }
1556 
1557  BIND(done, result);
1558  return result;
1559  }
1560  case TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kInt64: {
1561  DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions,
1562  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kBigInt);
1563  DCHECK(Is64());
1564  Label<Word64> done(this);
1565 
1566  V<Word32> bitfield = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
1567  object, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntBitfield());
1568  IF (__ Word32Equal(bitfield, 0)) {
1569  GOTO(done, 0);
1570  } ELSE {
1571  V<Word64> lsd = __ template LoadField<Word64>(
1572  object, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntLeastSignificantDigit64());
1573  V<Word32> sign =
1574  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield, BigInt::SignBits::kMask);
1575  IF (__ Word32Equal(sign, 1)) {
1576  GOTO(done, __ Word64Sub(0, lsd));
1577  }
1578 
1579  GOTO(done, lsd);
1580  }
1581 
1582  BIND(done, result);
1583  return result;
1584  }
1585  case TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kBit: {
1586  Label<Word32> done(this);
1587 
1588  if (input_assumptions ==
1589  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kObject) {
1590  // Perform Smi check.
1591  IF (UNLIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1592  GOTO(done, __ Word32Equal(__ TaggedEqual(object, __ TagSmi(0)), 0));
1593  }
1594 
1595  // Otherwise fall through into HeapObject case.
1596  } else {
1597  DCHECK_EQ(
1598  input_assumptions,
1599  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kHeapObject);
1600  }
1601 
1602 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
1603  // Check if {object} is a falsey root or the true value.
1604  // Undefined is the first root, so it's the smallest possible pointer
1605  // value, which means we don't have to subtract it for the range check.
1606  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate_);
1607  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kFirstAllocatedRoot ==
1608  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUndefinedValue);
1609  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUndefinedValue + sizeof(Undefined) ==
1610  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue);
1611  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue + sizeof(Null) ==
1612  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kempty_string);
1613  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kempty_string +
1614  SeqOneByteString::SizeFor(0) ==
1615  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kFalseValue);
1616  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kFalseValue + sizeof(False) ==
1617  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kTrueValue);
1618  V<Word32> object_as_word32 = __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(
1619  __ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(V<HeapObject>::Cast(object)));
1620  V<Word32> true_as_word32 =
1621  __ Word32Constant(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kTrueValue);
1622  GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThan(object_as_word32, true_as_word32), done, 0);
1623  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(object_as_word32, true_as_word32), done, 1);
1624 #else
1625  // Check if {object} is false.
1626  GOTO_IF(
1627  __ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(factory_->false_value())),
1628  done, 0);
1629 
1630  // Check if {object} is true.
1631  GOTO_IF(__ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(factory_->true_value())),
1632  done, 1);
1633 
1634  // Check if {object} is the empty string.
1635  GOTO_IF(
1636  __ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(factory_->empty_string())),
1637  done, 0);
1638 
1639  // Only check null and undefined if we're not going to check the
1640  // undetectable bit.
1641  if (DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector()) {
1642  // Check if {object} is the null value.
1643  GOTO_IF(
1644  __ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(factory_->null_value())),
1645  done, 0);
1646 
1647  // Check if {object} is the undefined value.
1648  GOTO_IF(__ TaggedEqual(object,
1649  __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_value())),
1650  done, 0);
1651  }
1652 #endif
1653 
1654  // Load the map of {object}.
1655  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
1656 
1657  if (!DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector()) {
1658  // Check if the {object} is undetectable and immediately return false.
1659  V<Word32> bitfield = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
1660  map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField());
1661  GOTO_IF(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
1662  Map::Bits1::IsUndetectableBit::kMask),
1663  done, 0);
1664  }
1665 
1666  // Check if {object} is a HeapNumber.
1667  IF (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
1668  map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())))) {
1669  // For HeapNumber {object}, just check that its value is not 0.0, -0.0
1670  // or NaN.
1671  V<Float64> number_value =
1672  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(object));
1673  GOTO(done, __ Float64LessThan(0.0, __ Float64Abs(number_value)));
1674  }
1675 
1676  // Check if {object} is a BigInt.
1677  IF (UNLIKELY(
1678  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->bigint_map())))) {
1679  V<Word32> bitfield = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
1680  object, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntBitfield());
1681  GOTO(done, IsNonZero(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
1682  BigInt::LengthBits::kMask)));
1683  }
1684 
1685  // All other values that reach here are true.
1686  GOTO(done, 1);
1687 
1688  BIND(done, result);
1689  return result;
1690  }
1691  }
1692  UNREACHABLE();
1693  }

1695  V<Word> REDUCE(TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeopt)(
1696  V<JSPrimitive> input, V<FrameState> frame_state,
1697  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind kind,
1698  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::InputRequirement
1699  input_requirement,
1700  const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
1701  DCHECK_EQ(kind,
1702  TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32);
1703  Label<Word32> done(this);
1704  // In the Smi case, just convert to int32.
1705  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(input)), done,
1706  __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(input)));
1707 
1708  // Otherwise, check that it's a heap number or oddball and truncate the
1709  // value to int32.
1710  V<Float64> number_value = ConvertHeapObjectToFloat64OrDeopt(
1711  input, frame_state, input_requirement, feedback);
1712  GOTO(done, __ JSTruncateFloat64ToWord32(number_value));
1713 
1714  BIND(done, result);
1715  return result;
1716  }

1718  V<Word32> JSAnyIsNotPrimitiveHeapObject(
1719  V<Object> value, V<Map> value_map = V<Map>::Invalid()) {
1720  if (!value_map.valid()) {
1721  value_map = __ LoadMapField(value);
1722  }
1723 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
1724  // Assumes only primitive objects and JS_RECEIVER's are passed here. All
1725  // primitive object's maps are in RO space and are allocated before all
1726  // JS_RECEIVER maps. Thus primitive object maps have smaller (compressed)
1727  // addresses.
1728  return __ Uint32LessThan(
1729  InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit,
1730  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(value_map)));
1731 #else
1732  static_assert(LAST_TYPE == LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
1733  V<Word32> value_instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(value_map);
1734  return __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE,
1735  value_instance_type);
1736 #endif
1737  }

1739  V<Object> REDUCE(ConvertJSPrimitiveToObject)(V<JSPrimitive> value,
1740  V<Context> native_context,
1741  V<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy,
1742  ConvertReceiverMode mode) {
1743  switch (mode) {
1744  case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
1745  return global_proxy;
1746  case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
1747  case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny: {
1748  Label<Object> done(this);
1749 
1750  // Check if {value} is already a JSReceiver (or null/undefined).
1751  Label<> convert_to_object(this);
1752  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(value)), convert_to_object);
1753  GOTO_IF_NOT(LIKELY(__ JSAnyIsNotPrimitiveHeapObject(value)),
1754  convert_to_object);
1755  GOTO(done, value);
1756 
1757  // Wrap the primitive {value} into a JSPrimitiveWrapper.
1758  if (BIND(convert_to_object)) {
1759  if (mode != ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined) {
1760  // Replace the {value} with the {global_proxy}.
1761  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
1762  value, __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_value()))),
1763  done, global_proxy);
1764  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
1765  value, __ HeapConstant(factory_->null_value()))),
1766  done, global_proxy);
1767  }
1768  GOTO(done, __ CallBuiltin_ToObject(isolate_, native_context, value));
1769  }
1770 
1771  BIND(done, result);
1772  return result;
1773  }
1774  }
1775  UNREACHABLE();
1776  }

1778  enum class StringEncoding { kOneByte, kTwoByte, kUnknown };
1779  StringEncoding GetStringEncoding(V<String> string) {
1780  const ConstantOp* constant =
1781  __ Get(string).template TryCast<Opmask::kHeapConstant>();
1782  if (!constant) return StringEncoding::kUnknown;
1783 
1784  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded unpark(broker_);
1785  HeapObjectRef ref = MakeRef(broker_, constant->handle());
1786  if (!V8_LIKELY(ref.IsString())) {
1787  // This can only happen in unreachable code.
1788  return StringEncoding::kUnknown;
1789  }
1790 
1791  return ref.AsString().IsOneByteRepresentation() ? StringEncoding::kOneByte
1792  : StringEncoding::kTwoByte;
1793  }

1795  V<ConsString> REDUCE(NewConsString)(V<Word32> length, V<String> first,
1796  V<String> second) {
1797  ScopedVar<Map> map(this);
1798 
1799  // Determine the instance types of {first} and {second}.
1800  StringEncoding first_encoding = GetStringEncoding(first);
1801  StringEncoding second_encoding = GetStringEncoding(second);
1802 
1803  // Determine the proper map for the resulting ConsString.
1804  // If either of {first} or {second} is a 2-byte string, then we create a
1805  // 2-byte string. If both {first} and {second} are one-byte strings, we
1806  // create a new 1-byte string.
1807  if (first_encoding == StringEncoding::kTwoByte ||
1808  second_encoding == StringEncoding::kTwoByte) {
1809  map = __ HeapConstant(factory_->cons_two_byte_string_map());
1810  } else if (first_encoding == StringEncoding::kOneByte &&
1811  second_encoding == StringEncoding::kOneByte) {
1812  map = __ HeapConstant(factory_->cons_one_byte_string_map());
1813  } else {
1814  V<Word32> first_type, second_type;
1815  constexpr int kAllOnesMask = -1;
1816  if (first_encoding == StringEncoding::kUnknown) {
1817  V<Map> first_map = __ LoadMapField(first);
1818  first_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(first_map);
1819  } else {
1820  DCHECK_EQ(first_encoding, StringEncoding::kOneByte);
1821  first_type = __ Word32Constant(kAllOnesMask);
1822  }
1823  if (second_encoding == StringEncoding::kUnknown) {
1824  V<Map> second_map = __ LoadMapField(second);
1825  second_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(second_map);
1826  } else {
1827  DCHECK_EQ(second_encoding, StringEncoding::kOneByte);
1828  second_type = __ Word32Constant(kAllOnesMask);
1829  }
1830 
1831  static_assert(kOneByteStringTag != 0);
1832  static_assert(kTwoByteStringTag == 0);
1833  V<Word32> instance_type = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(first_type, second_type);
1834  V<Word32> encoding =
1835  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kStringEncodingMask);
1836  IF (__ Word32Equal(encoding, kTwoByteStringTag)) {
1837  map = __ HeapConstant(factory_->cons_two_byte_string_map());
1838  } ELSE {
1839  map = __ HeapConstant(factory_->cons_one_byte_string_map());
1840  }
1841  }
1842 
1843  // Allocate the resulting ConsString.
1844  auto string = __ template Allocate<ConsString>(
1845  __ IntPtrConstant(sizeof(ConsString)), AllocationType::kYoung,
1846  kTaggedAligned);
1847  __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilder::ForMap(), map);
1848  __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilder::ForNameRawHashField(),
1849  __ Word32Constant(Name::kEmptyHashField));
1850  __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength(), length);
1851  __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilder::ForConsStringFirst(), first);
1852  __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilder::ForConsStringSecond(), second);
1853  return __ FinishInitialization(std::move(string));
1854  }
1855 
1856  V<AnyFixedArray> REDUCE(NewArray)(V<WordPtr> length, NewArrayOp::Kind kind,
1857  AllocationType allocation_type) {
1858  Label<AnyFixedArray> done(this);
1859 
1860  GOTO_IF(__ WordPtrEqual(length, 0), done,
1861  __ HeapConstant(factory_->empty_fixed_array()));
1862 
1863  // Compute the effective size of the backing store.
1864  intptr_t size_log2;
1865  Handle<Map> array_map;
1866  // TODO(nicohartmann@): Replace ElementAccess by a Turboshaft replacement.
1867  ElementAccess access;
1868  V<Any> the_hole_value;
1869  switch (kind) {
1870  case NewArrayOp::Kind::kDouble: {
1871  size_log2 = kDoubleSizeLog2;
1872  array_map = factory_->fixed_double_array_map();
1873  access = {kTaggedBase, OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedDoubleArray),
1874  compiler::Type::NumberOrHole(), MachineType::Float64(),
1875  kNoWriteBarrier};
1876  the_hole_value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1877  __ HeapConstant(factory_->the_hole_value()),
1878  AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1879  break;
1880  }
1881  case NewArrayOp::Kind::kObject: {
1882  size_log2 = kTaggedSizeLog2;
1883  array_map = factory_->fixed_array_map();
1884  access = {kTaggedBase, OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray),
1885  compiler::Type::Any(), MachineType::AnyTagged(),
1886  kNoWriteBarrier};
1887  the_hole_value = __ HeapConstant(factory_->the_hole_value());
1888  break;
1889  }
1890  }
1891  V<WordPtr> size =
1892  __ WordPtrAdd(__ WordPtrShiftLeft(length, static_cast<int>(size_log2)),
1893  access.header_size);
1894 
1895  // Allocate the result and initialize the header.
1896  auto uninitialized_array = __ template Allocate<AnyFixedArray>(
1897  size, allocation_type, kTaggedAligned);
1898  __ InitializeField(uninitialized_array, AccessBuilder::ForMap(),
1899  __ HeapConstant(array_map));
1900  __ InitializeField(uninitialized_array,
1901  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength(),
1902  __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(length)));
1903  // TODO(nicohartmann@): Should finish initialization only after all elements
1904  // have been initialized.
1905  auto array = __ FinishInitialization(std::move(uninitialized_array));
1906 
1907  ScopedVar<WordPtr> index(this, 0);
1908 
1909  WHILE(__ UintPtrLessThan(index, length)) {
1910  __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(array, access, index, the_hole_value);
1911  // Advance the {index}.
1912  index = __ WordPtrAdd(index, 1);
1913  }
1914 
1915  GOTO(done, array);
1916 
1917  BIND(done, result);
1918  return result;
1919  }
1920 
1921  V<Number> REDUCE(DoubleArrayMinMax)(V<JSArray> array,
1922  DoubleArrayMinMaxOp::Kind kind) {
1923  DCHECK(kind == DoubleArrayMinMaxOp::Kind::kMin ||
1924  kind == DoubleArrayMinMaxOp::Kind::kMax);
1925  const bool is_max = kind == DoubleArrayMinMaxOp::Kind::kMax;
1926 
1927  // Iterate the elements and find the result.
1928  V<WordPtr> array_length =
1929  __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(__ template LoadField<Smi>(
1930  array, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(
1931  ElementsKind::PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS))));
1932  V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
1933  array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
1934 
1935  ScopedVar<Float64> result(this, is_max ? -V8_INFINITY : V8_INFINITY);
1936  ScopedVar<WordPtr> index(this, 0);
1937 
1938  WHILE(__ UintPtrLessThan(index, array_length)) {
1939  V<Float64> element = __ template LoadNonArrayBufferElement<Float64>(
1940  elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), index);
1941 
1942  result = is_max ? __ Float64Max(result, element)
1943  : __ Float64Min(result, element);
1944  index = __ WordPtrAdd(index, 1);
1945  }
1946 
1947  return __ ConvertFloat64ToNumber(result,
1948  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero);
1949  }
