1951  V<Object> REDUCE(LoadFieldByIndex)(V<Object> object, V<Word32> field_index) {
1952  // Index encoding (see `src/objects/field-index-inl.h`):
1953  // For efficiency, the LoadByFieldIndex instruction takes an index that is
1954  // optimized for quick access. If the property is inline, the index is
1955  // positive. If it's out-of-line, the encoded index is -raw_index - 1 to
1956  // disambiguate the zero out-of-line index from the zero inobject case.
1957  // The index itself is shifted up by one bit, the lower-most bit
1958  // signifying if the field is a mutable double box (1) or not (0).
1959  V<WordPtr> index = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(field_index);
1960 
1961  Label<> double_field(this);
1962  Label<Object> done(this);
1963 
1964  // Check if field is a mutable double field.
1965  GOTO_IF(
1966  UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(
1967  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(index), 0x1), 0x1)),
1968  double_field);
1969 
1970  {
1971  // The field is a proper Tagged field on {object}. The {index} is
1972  // shifted to the left by one in the code below.
1973 
1974  // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object.
1975  IF (__ IntPtrLessThan(index, 0)) {
1976  // The field is located in the properties backing store of {object}.
1977  // The {index} is equal to the negated out of property index plus 1.
1978  V<Object> properties = __ template LoadField<Object>(
1979  object, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer());
1980 
1981  V<WordPtr> out_of_object_index = __ WordPtrSub(0, index);
1982  V<Object> result =
1983  __ Load(properties, out_of_object_index,
1984  LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase),
1985  MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(),
1986  OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kTaggedSize,
1987  kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1);
1988  GOTO(done, result);
1989  } ELSE {
1990  // This field is located in the {object} itself.
1991  V<Object> result = __ Load(
1992  object, index, LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase),
1993  MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(), JSObject::kHeaderSize,
1994  kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1);
1995  GOTO(done, result);
1996  }
1997  }
1998 
1999  if (BIND(double_field)) {
2000  // If field is a Double field, either unboxed in the object on 64 bit
2001  // architectures, or a mutable HeapNumber.
2002  V<WordPtr> double_index = __ WordPtrShiftRightArithmetic(index, 1);
2003  Label<Object> loaded_field(this);
2004 
2005  // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object.
2006  IF (__ IntPtrLessThan(double_index, 0)) {
2007  V<Object> properties = __ template LoadField<Object>(
2008  object, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer());
2009 
2010  V<WordPtr> out_of_object_index = __ WordPtrSub(0, double_index);
2011  V<Object> result = __ Load(
2012  properties, out_of_object_index,
2013  LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase),
2014  MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(),
2015  OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kTaggedSize, kTaggedSizeLog2);
2016  GOTO(loaded_field, result);
2017  } ELSE {
2018  // The field is located in the {object} itself.
2019  V<Object> result =
2020  __ Load(object, double_index,
2021  LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase),
2022  MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(), JSObject::kHeaderSize,
2023  kTaggedSizeLog2);
2024  GOTO(loaded_field, result);
2025  }
2026 
2027  if (BIND(loaded_field, field)) {
2028  // We may have transitioned in-place away from double, so check that
2029  // this is a HeapNumber -- otherwise the load is fine and we don't need
2030  // to copy anything anyway.
2031  GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(field), done, field);
2032  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(field);
2033  GOTO_IF_NOT(
2034  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
2035  done, field);
2036 
2037  V<Float64> value = __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(field));
2038  GOTO(done, AllocateHeapNumber(value));
2039  }
2040  }
2041 
2042  BIND(done, result);
2043  return result;
2044  }
2045 
2046  V<Word> REDUCE(WordBinopDeoptOnOverflow)(
2047  V<Word> left, V<Word> right, V<FrameState> frame_state,
2048  WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind kind, WordRepresentation rep,
2049  FeedbackSource feedback, CheckForMinusZeroMode mode) {
2050  switch (kind) {
2051  case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kSignedAdd: {
2052  DCHECK_EQ(mode, CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
2053  V<Tuple<Word, Word32>> result =
2054  __ IntAddCheckOverflow(left, right, rep);
2055 
2056  V<Word32> overflow = __ template Projection<1>(result);
2057  __ DeoptimizeIf(overflow, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow,
2058  feedback);
2059  return __ template Projection<0>(result, rep);
2060  }
2061  case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kSignedSub: {
2062  DCHECK_EQ(mode, CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
2063  V<Tuple<Word, Word32>> result =
2064  __ IntSubCheckOverflow(left, right, rep);
2065 
2066  V<Word32> overflow = __ template Projection<1>(result);
2067  __ DeoptimizeIf(overflow, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow,
2068  feedback);
2069  return __ template Projection<0>(result, rep);
2070  }
2071  case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kSignedMul:
2072  if (rep == WordRepresentation::Word32()) {
2073  V<Word32> left_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(left);
2074  V<Word32> right_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(right);
2075  V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> result =
2076  __ Int32MulCheckOverflow(left_w32, right_w32);
2077  V<Word32> overflow = __ template Projection<1>(result);
2078  __ DeoptimizeIf(overflow, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow,
2079  feedback);
2080  V<Word32> value = __ template Projection<0>(result);
2081 
2082  if (mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
2083  IF (__ Word32Equal(value, 0)) {
2084  __ DeoptimizeIf(
2085  __ Int32LessThan(__ Word32BitwiseOr(left_w32, right_w32), 0),
2086  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
2087  }
2088  }
2089 
2090  return value;
2091  } else {
2092  DCHECK_EQ(rep, WordRepresentation::Word64());
2093  DCHECK_EQ(mode, CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
2094  V<Tuple<Word64, Word32>> result = __ Int64MulCheckOverflow(
2095  V<Word64>::Cast(left), V<Word64>::Cast(right));
2096 
2097  V<Word32> overflow = __ template Projection<1>(result);
2098  __ DeoptimizeIf(overflow, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow,
2099  feedback);
2100  return __ template Projection<0>(result);
2101  }
2102  case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kSignedDiv:
2103  if (rep == WordRepresentation::Word32()) {
2104  V<Word32> left_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(left);
2105  V<Word32> right_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(right);
2106  // Check if the {rhs} is a known power of two.
2107  int32_t divisor;
2108  if (__ matcher().MatchPowerOfTwoWord32Constant(right_w32, &divisor)) {
2109  // Since we know that {rhs} is a power of two, we can perform a fast
2110  // check to see if the relevant least significant bits of the {lhs}
2111  // are all zero, and if so we know that we can perform a division
2112  // safely (and fast by doing an arithmetic - aka sign preserving -
2113  // right shift on {lhs}).
2114  V<Word32> check =
2115  __ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(left_w32, divisor - 1), 0);
2116  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state,
2117  DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
2118  return __ Word32ShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros(
2119  left_w32, base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(divisor));
2120  } else {
2121  Label<Word32> done(this);
2122 
2123  // Check if {rhs} is positive (and not zero).
2124  IF (__ Int32LessThan(0, right_w32)) {
2125  GOTO(done, __ Int32Div(left_w32, right_w32));
2126  } ELSE {
2127  // Check if {rhs} is zero.
2128  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(right_w32, 0), frame_state,
2129  DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
2130 
2131  // Check if {lhs} is zero, as that would produce minus zero.
2132  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(left_w32, 0), frame_state,
2133  DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
2134 
2135  // Check if {lhs} is kMinInt and {rhs} is -1, in which case we'd
2136  // have to return -kMinInt, which is not representable as Word32.
2137  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(left_w32, kMinInt))) {
2138  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(right_w32, -1), frame_state,
2139  DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow, feedback);
2140  }
2141 
2142  GOTO(done, __ Int32Div(left_w32, right_w32));
2143  }
2144 
2145  BIND(done, value);
2146  V<Word32> lossless =
2147  __ Word32Equal(left_w32, __ Word32Mul(value, right_w32));
2148  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(lossless, frame_state,
2149  DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
2150  return value;
2151  }
2152  } else {
2153  DCHECK_EQ(rep, WordRepresentation::Word64());
2154  DCHECK(Is64());
2155  V<Word64> left_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(left);
2156  V<Word64> right_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(right);
2157 
2158  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word64Equal(right_w64, 0), frame_state,
2159  DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
2160  // Check if {lhs} is kMinInt64 and {rhs} is -1, in which case we'd
2161  // have to return -kMinInt64, which is not representable as Word64.
2162  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word64Equal(left_w64,
2163  std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()))) {
2164  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word64Equal(right_w64, int64_t{-1}), frame_state,
2165  DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow, feedback);
2166  }
2167 
2168  return __ Int64Div(left_w64, right_w64);
2169  }
2170  case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kSignedMod:
2171  if (rep == WordRepresentation::Word32()) {
2172  V<Word32> left_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(left);
2173  V<Word32> right_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(right);
2174  // General case for signed integer modulus, with optimization for
2175  // (unknown) power of 2 right hand side.
2176  //
2177  // if rhs <= 0 then
2178  // rhs = -rhs
2179  // deopt if rhs == 0
2180  // if lhs < 0 then
2181  // let lhs_abs = -lhs in
2182  // let res = lhs_abs % rhs in
2183  // deopt if res == 0
2184  // -res
2185  // else
2186  // let msk = rhs - 1 in
2187  // if rhs & msk == 0 then
2188  // lhs & msk
2189  // else
2190  // lhs % rhs
2191  //
2192  Label<Word32> rhs_checked(this);
2193  Label<Word32> done(this);
2194 
2195  // Check if {rhs} is not strictly positive.
2196  IF (__ Int32LessThanOrEqual(right_w32, 0)) {
2197  // Negate {rhs}, might still produce a negative result in case of
2198  // -2^31, but that is handled safely below.
2199  V<Word32> temp = __ Word32Sub(0, right_w32);
2200 
2201  // Ensure that {rhs} is not zero, otherwise we'd have to return NaN.
2202  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(temp, frame_state,
2203  DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
2204  GOTO(rhs_checked, temp);
2205  } ELSE {
2206  GOTO(rhs_checked, right_w32);
2207  }
2208 
2209  BIND(rhs_checked, rhs_value);
2210 
2211  IF (__ Int32LessThan(left_w32, 0)) {
2212  // The {lhs} is a negative integer. This is very unlikely and
2213  // we intentionally don't use the BuildUint32Mod() here, which
2214  // would try to figure out whether {rhs} is a power of two,
2215  // since this is intended to be a slow-path.
2216  V<Word32> temp = __ Uint32Mod(__ Word32Sub(0, left_w32), rhs_value);
2217 
2218  // Check if we would have to return -0.
2219  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(temp, 0), frame_state,
2220  DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
2221  GOTO(done, __ Word32Sub(0, temp));
2222  } ELSE {
2223  // The {lhs} is a non-negative integer.
2224  GOTO(done, BuildUint32Mod(left_w32, rhs_value));
2225  }
2226 
2227  BIND(done, result);
2228  return result;
2229  } else {
2230  DCHECK_EQ(rep, WordRepresentation::Word64());
2231  DCHECK(Is64());
2232  V<Word64> left_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(left);
2233  V<Word64> right_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(right);
2234 
2235  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word64Equal(right_w64, 0), frame_state,
2236  DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
2237 
2238  // While the mod-result cannot overflow, the underlying instruction is
2239  // `idiv` and will trap when the accompanying div-result overflows.
2240  IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word64Equal(left_w64,
2241  std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()))) {
2242  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word64Equal(right_w64, int64_t{-1}), frame_state,
2243  DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow, feedback);
2244  }
2245 
2246  return __ Int64Mod(left_w64, right_w64);
2247  }
2248  case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kUnsignedDiv: {
2249  DCHECK_EQ(rep, WordRepresentation::Word32());
2250  V<Word32> left_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(left);
2251  V<Word32> right_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(right);
2252 
2253  // Check if the {rhs} is a known power of two.
2254  int32_t divisor;
2255  if (__ matcher().MatchPowerOfTwoWord32Constant(right_w32, &divisor)) {
2256  // Since we know that {rhs} is a power of two, we can perform a fast
2257  // check to see if the relevant least significant bits of the {lhs}
2258  // are all zero, and if so we know that we can perform a division
2259  // safely (and fast by doing a logical - aka zero extending - right
2260  // shift on {lhs}).
2261  V<Word32> check =
2262  __ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(left_w32, divisor - 1), 0);
2263  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state,
2264  DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
2265  return __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(
2266  left_w32, base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(divisor));
2267  } else {
2268  // Ensure that {rhs} is not zero, otherwise we'd have to return NaN.
2269  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(right_w32, 0), frame_state,
2270  DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
2271 
2272  // Perform the actual unsigned integer division.
2273  V<Word32> value = __ Uint32Div(left_w32, right_w32);
2274 
2275  // Check if the remainder is non-zero.
2276  V<Word32> lossless =
2277  __ Word32Equal(left_w32, __ Word32Mul(right_w32, value));
2278  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(lossless, frame_state,
2279  DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
2280  return value;
2281  }
2282  }
2283  case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kUnsignedMod: {
2284  DCHECK_EQ(rep, WordRepresentation::Word32());
2285  V<Word32> left_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(left);
2286  V<Word32> right_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(right);
2287 
2288  // Ensure that {rhs} is not zero, otherwise we'd have to return NaN.
2289  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(right_w32, 0), frame_state,
2290  DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
2291 
2292  return BuildUint32Mod(left_w32, right_w32);
2293  }
2294  }
2295  }
2296 
2297  V<BigInt> REDUCE(BigIntBinop)(V<BigInt> left, V<BigInt> right,
2298  V<FrameState> frame_state,
2299  BigIntBinopOp::Kind kind) {
2300  const Builtin builtin = GetBuiltinForBigIntBinop(kind);
2301  switch (kind) {
2302  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kAdd:
2303  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kSub:
2304  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseAnd:
2305  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseXor:
2306  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kShiftLeft:
2307  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic: {
2308  V<Numeric> result = CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(builtin, {left, right});
2309 
2310  // Check for exception sentinel: Smi 0 is returned to signal
2311  // BigIntTooBig.
2312  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ ObjectIsSmi(result), frame_state,
2313  DeoptimizeReason::kBigIntTooBig, FeedbackSource{});
2314  return V<BigInt>::Cast(result);
2315  }
2316  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kMul:
2317  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kDiv:
2318  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kMod: {
2319  V<Numeric> result = CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(builtin, {left, right});
2320 
2321  // Check for exception sentinel: Smi 1 is returned to signal
2322  // TerminationRequested.
2323  IF (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(result, __ TagSmi(1)))) {
2324  __ CallRuntime_TerminateExecution(isolate_, frame_state,
2325  __ NoContextConstant());
2326  }
2327 
2328  // Check for exception sentinel: Smi 0 is returned to signal
2329  // BigIntTooBig or DivisionByZero.
2330  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ ObjectIsSmi(result), frame_state,
2331  kind == BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kMul
2332  ? DeoptimizeReason::kBigIntTooBig
2333  : DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero,
2334  FeedbackSource{});
2335  return V<BigInt>::Cast(result);
2336  }
2337  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseOr: {
2338  return CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(builtin, {left, right});
2339  }
2340  default:
2341  UNIMPLEMENTED();
2342  }
2343  UNREACHABLE();
2344  }
2345 
2346  V<Boolean> REDUCE(BigIntComparison)(V<BigInt> left, V<BigInt> right,
2347  BigIntComparisonOp::Kind kind) {
2348  switch (kind) {
2349  case BigIntComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual:
2350  return CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(Builtin::kBigIntEqual, {left, right});
2351  case BigIntComparisonOp::Kind::kLessThan:
2352  return CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(Builtin::kBigIntLessThan, {left, right});
2353  case BigIntComparisonOp::Kind::kLessThanOrEqual:
2354  return CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(Builtin::kBigIntLessThanOrEqual,
2355  {left, right});
2356  }
2357  }

2364  V<Word32> REDUCE(StringAt)(V<String> string, V<WordPtr> pos,
2365  StringAtOp::Kind kind) {
2366  if (kind == StringAtOp::Kind::kCharCode) {
2367  Label<Word32> done(this);
2368 
2369  if (const ConstantOp* cst =
2370  __ matcher().template TryCast<ConstantOp>(string);
2371  cst && cst->kind == ConstantOp::Kind::kHeapObject) {
2372  // For constant SeqString, we have a fast-path that doesn't run through
2373  // the loop. It requires fewer loads (we only load the map once, but not
2374  // the instance type), uses static 1/2-byte, and only uses a single
2375  // comparison to check that the string has indeed the correct SeqString
2376  // map.
2377  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded unpark(broker_);
2378  HeapObjectRef ref = MakeRef(broker_, cst->handle());
2379  if (ref.IsString()) {
2380  StringRef str = ref.AsString();
2381  if (str.IsSeqString()) {
2382  V<Map> dynamic_map = __ LoadMapField(string);
2383  Handle<Map> expected_map = str.map(broker_).object();
2384  IF (__ TaggedEqual(dynamic_map, __ HeapConstant(expected_map))) {
2385  bool one_byte = str.IsOneByteRepresentation();
2386  GOTO(done,
2387  LoadFromSeqString(string, pos, __ Word32Constant(one_byte)));
2388  }
2389  }
2390  }
2391  }
2392 
2393  Label<> seq_string(this), external_string(this), cons_string(this),
2394  sliced_string(this), thin_string(this);
2395  // TODO(dmercadier): the runtime label should be deferred, and because
2396  // Labels/Blocks don't have deferred annotation, we achieve this by
2397  // marking all branches to this Label as UNLIKELY, but 1) it's easy to
2398  // forget one, and 2) it makes the code less clear: `if(x) {} else
2399  // if(likely(y)) {} else {}` looks like `y` is more likely than `x`, but
2400  // it just means that `y` is more likely than `!y`.
2401  Label<> runtime(this);
2402  // We need a loop here to properly deal with indirect strings
2403  // (SlicedString, ConsString and ThinString).
2404  LoopLabel<> loop(this);
2405  ScopedVar<String> receiver(this, string);
2406  ScopedVar<WordPtr> position(this, pos);
2407  GOTO(loop);
2408 
2409  BIND_LOOP(loop) {
2410  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(receiver);
2411 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2412  V<Word32> map_bits =
2413  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(map));
2414 
2415  using StringTypeRange =
2416  InstanceTypeChecker::kUniqueMapRangeOfStringType;
2417  // Check the string map ranges in dense increasing order, to avoid
2418  // needing to subtract away the lower bound.
2419  static_assert(StringTypeRange::kSeqString.first == 0);
2420  GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(map_bits,
2421  StringTypeRange::kSeqString.second),
2422  seq_string);
2423 
2424  static_assert(StringTypeRange::kSeqString.second + Map::kSize ==
2425  StringTypeRange::kExternalString.first);
2426  GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
2427  map_bits, StringTypeRange::kExternalString.second),
2428  external_string);
2429 
2430  static_assert(StringTypeRange::kExternalString.second + Map::kSize ==
2431  StringTypeRange::kConsString.first);
2432  GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(map_bits,
2433  StringTypeRange::kConsString.second),
2434  cons_string);
2435 
2436  static_assert(StringTypeRange::kConsString.second + Map::kSize ==
2437  StringTypeRange::kSlicedString.first);
2438  GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(map_bits,
2439  StringTypeRange::kSlicedString.second),
2440  sliced_string);
2441 
2442  static_assert(StringTypeRange::kSlicedString.second + Map::kSize ==
2443  StringTypeRange::kThinString.first);
2444  GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(map_bits,
2445  StringTypeRange::kThinString.second),
2446  thin_string);
2447 #else
2448  V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
2449  V<Word32> representation =
2450  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kStringRepresentationMask);
2451 
2452  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(representation, kSeqStringTag), seq_string);
2453  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(representation, kExternalStringTag),
2454  external_string);
2455  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(representation, kConsStringTag), cons_string);
2456  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(representation, kSlicedStringTag),
2457  sliced_string);
2458  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(representation, kThinStringTag), thin_string);
2459 #endif
2460 
2461  __ Unreachable();
2462 
2463  if (BIND(seq_string)) {
2464 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2465  V<Word32> is_one_byte = __ Word32Equal(
2466  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(map_bits,
2467  InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapEncodingMask),
2468  InstanceTypeChecker::kOneByteStringMapBit);
2469 #else
2470  V<Word32> is_one_byte = __ Word32Equal(
2471  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kStringEncodingMask),
2472  kOneByteStringTag);
2473 #endif
2474  GOTO(done, LoadFromSeqString(receiver, position, is_one_byte));
2475  }
2476 
2477  if (BIND(external_string)) {
2478  // We need to bailout to the runtime for uncached external
2479  // strings.
2480 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2481  V<Word32> is_uncached_external_string = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
2482  __ Word32Sub(map_bits,
2483  StringTypeRange::kUncachedExternalString.first),
2484  StringTypeRange::kUncachedExternalString.second -
2485  StringTypeRange::kUncachedExternalString.first);
2486 #else
2487  V<Word32> is_uncached_external_string = __ Word32Equal(
2488  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kUncachedExternalStringMask),
2489  kUncachedExternalStringTag);
2490 #endif
2491  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(is_uncached_external_string), runtime);
2492 
2493  OpIndex data = __ LoadField(
2494  receiver, AccessBuilder::ForExternalStringResourceData());
2495 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2496  V<Word32> is_two_byte = __ Word32Equal(
2497  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(map_bits,
2498  InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapEncodingMask),
2499  InstanceTypeChecker::kTwoByteStringMapBit);
2500 #else
2501  V<Word32> is_two_byte = __ Word32Equal(
2502  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kStringEncodingMask),
2503  kTwoByteStringTag);
2504 #endif
2505  IF (is_two_byte) {
2506  constexpr uint8_t twobyte_size_log2 = 1;
2507  V<Word32> value =
2508  __ Load(data, position,
2509  LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kUntaggedBase),
2510  MemoryRepresentation::Uint16(), 0, twobyte_size_log2);
2511  GOTO(done, value);
2512  } ELSE {
2513  constexpr uint8_t onebyte_size_log2 = 0;
2514  V<Word32> value =
2515  __ Load(data, position,
2516  LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kUntaggedBase),
2517  MemoryRepresentation::Uint8(), 0, onebyte_size_log2);
2518  GOTO(done, value);
2519  }
2520  }
2521 
2522  if (BIND(cons_string)) {
2523  V<String> second = __ template LoadField<String>(
2524  receiver, AccessBuilder::ForConsStringSecond());
2525  GOTO_IF_NOT(LIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
2526  second, __ HeapConstant(factory_->empty_string()))),
2527  runtime);
2528  receiver = __ template LoadField<String>(
2529  receiver, AccessBuilder::ForConsStringFirst());
2530  GOTO(loop);
2531  }
2532 
2533  if (BIND(sliced_string)) {
2534  V<Smi> offset = __ template LoadField<Smi>(
2535  receiver, AccessBuilder::ForSlicedStringOffset());
2536  receiver = __ template LoadField<String>(
2537  receiver, AccessBuilder::ForSlicedStringParent());
2538  position = __ WordPtrAdd(position,
2539  __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(offset)));
2540  GOTO(loop);
2541  }
2542 
2543  if (BIND(thin_string)) {
2544  receiver = __ template LoadField<String>(
2545  receiver, AccessBuilder::ForThinStringActual());
2546  GOTO(loop);
2547  }
2548 
2549  if (BIND(runtime)) {
2550  V<Word32> value =
2551  __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(__ CallRuntime_StringCharCodeAt(
2552  isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), receiver,
2553  __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(position)))));
2554  GOTO(done, value);
2555  }
2556  }
2557 
2558  BIND(done, result);
2559  return result;
2560  } else {
2561  DCHECK_EQ(kind, StringAtOp::Kind::kCodePoint);
2562  return LoadSurrogatePairAt(string, {}, pos, UnicodeEncoding::UTF32);
2563  }
2564 
2565  UNREACHABLE();
2566  }

2571  return __ template LoadField<Word32>(string,
2572  AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());

2645  V<Boolean> REDUCE(StringOrOddballStrictEqual)(V<HeapObject> left,
2646  V<HeapObject> right) {
2647  Label<Boolean> done(this);
2648 
2649  GOTO_IF(__ TaggedEqual(left, right), done,
2650  __ HeapConstant(factory_->true_value()));
2651

2653  // is not a string, then they must be non-equal (they cannot be the

2655

2659  __ HeapConstant(factory_->false_value()));
2660 
2661  V<Map> right_map = __ LoadMapField(right);
2662  V<Word32> right_instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(right_map);
2663  GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(right_instance_type, ODDBALL_TYPE), done,
2664  __ HeapConstant(factory_->false_value()));

2673  void GenerateStringEqualBuiltinCall(V<String> left, V<String> right,
2674  Label<Boolean>* done) {
2675  V<Word32> left_length =
2676  __ template LoadField<Word32>(left, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());
2677  V<Word32> right_length =
2678  __ template LoadField<Word32>(right, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());
2679  IF (__ Word32Equal(left_length, right_length)) {
2680  GOTO(*done,
2681  __ CallBuiltin_StringEqual(isolate_, left, right,
2682  __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(left_length)));
2683  } ELSE {
2684  GOTO(*done, __ HeapConstant(factory_->false_value()));

2688  V<Smi> REDUCE(ArgumentsLength)(ArgumentsLengthOp::Kind kind,
2689  int formal_parameter_count) {
2690  V<WordPtr> count =
2691  __ LoadOffHeap(__ FramePointer(), StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset,
2692  MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr());
2693  V<WordPtr> arguments_length = __ WordPtrSub(count, kJSArgcReceiverSlots);
2694 
2695  if (kind == ArgumentsLengthOp::Kind::kArguments) {
2696  return __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(arguments_length));
2697  } else {
2698  DCHECK_EQ(kind, ArgumentsLengthOp::Kind::kRest);
2699  V<WordPtr> rest_length =
2700  __ WordPtrSub(arguments_length, formal_parameter_count);
2701  Label<WordPtr> done(this);
2702  IF (__ IntPtrLessThan(rest_length, 0)) {
2703  GOTO(done, 0);
2704  } ELSE {
2705  GOTO(done, rest_length);
2706  }
2707 
2708  BIND(done, value);
2709  return __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(value));
2710  }
2711  }

2746  V<Object> REDUCE(LoadStackArgument)(V<WordPtr> base, V<WordPtr> index) {
2747  // Note that this is a load of a Tagged value
2748  // (MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer()), but since it's on the stack
2749  // where stack slots are all kSystemPointerSize, we use kSystemPointerSize
2750  // for element_size_log2. On 64-bit plateforms with pointer compression,
2751  // this means that we're kinda loading a 32-bit value from an array of
2752  // 64-bit values.
2753 #if V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS && V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
2754  constexpr int offset =
2755  CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp - kSystemPointerSize + 4;
2756 #else
2757  constexpr int offset =
2758  CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp - kSystemPointerSize;
2759 #endif
2760  return __ Load(base, index, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
2761  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(), offset,
2762  kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
2763  }

2765  V<None> REDUCE(StoreTypedElement)(OpIndex buffer, V<Object> base,
2766  V<WordPtr> external, V<WordPtr> index,
2767  V<Any> value,
2768  ExternalArrayType array_type) {
2769  V<WordPtr> data_ptr = BuildTypedArrayDataPointer(base, external);
2770 
2771  // Perform the actual typed element access.
2772  __ StoreArrayBufferElement(
2773  data_ptr, AccessBuilder::ForTypedArrayElement(array_type, true), index,
2774  value);
2775 
2776  // We need to keep the {buffer} alive so that the GC will not release the
2777  // ArrayBuffer (if there's any) as long as we are still operating on it.
2778  __ Retain(buffer);
2779  return {};

2782  V<None> REDUCE(TransitionAndStoreArrayElement)(
2783  V<JSArray> array, V<WordPtr> index, OpIndex value,
2784  TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind kind, MaybeHandle<Map> fast_map,
2785  MaybeHandle<Map> double_map) {
2786  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(array);
2787  V<Word32> bitfield2 =
2788  __ template LoadField<Word32>(map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2());
2789  V<Word32> elements_kind = __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(
2790  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield2, Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask),
2791  Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift);
2792 
2793  switch (kind) {
2794  case TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kElement: {
2795  // Possibly transition array based on input and store.
2796  //
2797  // -- TRANSITION PHASE -----------------
2798  // kind = ElementsKind(array)
2799  // if value is not smi {
2800  // if kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS {
2801  // if value is heap number {
2802  // Transition array to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2803  // kind = HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2804  // } else {
2805  // Transition array to HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2806  // kind = HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2807  // }
2808  // } else if kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
2809  // if value is not heap number {
2810  // Transition array to HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2811  // kind = HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2812  // }
2813  // }
2814  // }
2815  //
2816  // -- STORE PHASE ----------------------
2817  // [make sure {kind} is up-to-date]
2818  // if kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
2819  // if value is smi {
2820  // float_value = convert smi to float
2821  // Store array[index] = float_value
2822  // } else {
2823  // float_value = value
2824  // Store array[index] = float_value
2825  // }
2826  // } else {
2827  // // kind is HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2828  // Store array[index] = value
2829  // }
2830  //
2831  Label<Word32> do_store(this);
2832  // We can store a smi anywhere.
2833  GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(value), do_store, elements_kind);
2834 
2835  // {value} is a HeapObject.
2836  IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, elements_kind))) {
2837  // Transition {array} from HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2838  // or to HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
2839  V<Map> value_map = __ LoadMapField(value);
2840  IF (__ TaggedEqual(value_map,
2841  __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()))) {
2842  // {value} is a HeapNumber.
2843  TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS,
2844  HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS,
2845  double_map.ToHandleChecked());
2846  GOTO(do_store, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
2847  } ELSE {
2848  TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS,
2849  fast_map.ToHandleChecked());
2850  GOTO(do_store, HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
2851  }
2852  }
2853 
2854  GOTO_IF_NOT(LIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_ELEMENTS, elements_kind)),
2855  do_store, elements_kind);
2856 
2857  // We have double elements kind. Only a HeapNumber can be stored
2858  // without effecting a transition.
2859  V<Map> value_map = __ LoadMapField(value);
2860  IF_NOT (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
2861  value_map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())))) {
2862  TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS,
2863  fast_map.ToHandleChecked());
2864  GOTO(do_store, HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
2865  }
2866 
2867  GOTO(do_store, elements_kind);
2868 
2869  BIND(do_store, store_kind);
2870  V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
2871  array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
2872  IF (__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_ELEMENTS, store_kind)) {
2873  // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
2874  IF (__ ObjectIsSmi(value)) {
2875  V<Float64> float_value =
2876  __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(value));
2877  __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2878  elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), index,
2879  float_value);
2880  } ELSE {
2881  V<Float64> float_value =
2882  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(value));
2883  __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2884  elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), index,
2885  __ Float64SilenceNaN(float_value));
2886  }
2887  } ELSE {
2888  // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
2889  __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2890  elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(HOLEY_ELEMENTS),
2891  index, value);
2892  }
2893 
2894  break;
2895  }
2896  case TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kNumberElement: {
2897  Label<> done(this);
2898  // Possibly transition array based on input and store.
2899  //
2900  // -- TRANSITION PHASE -----------------
2901  // kind = ElementsKind(array)
2902  // if kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS {
2903  // Transition array to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2904  // } else if kind != HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
2905  // if kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS {
2906  // Store value as a HeapNumber in array[index].
2907  // } else {
2908  // This is UNREACHABLE, execute a debug break.
2909  // }
2910  // }
2911  //
2912  // -- STORE PHASE ----------------------
2913  // Store array[index] = value (it's a float)
2914  //
2915  // {value} is a float64.
2916  IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, elements_kind))) {
2917  // Transition {array} from HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS to
2918  // HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
2919  TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS,
2920  double_map.ToHandleChecked());
2921  } ELSE {
2922  // We expect that our input array started at HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, and
2923  // climbs the lattice up to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS. However, loop
2924  // peeling can break this assumption, because in the peeled iteration,
2925  // the array might have transitioned to HOLEY_ELEMENTS kind, so we
2926  // handle this as well.
2927  IF_NOT (LIKELY(
2928  __ Word32Equal(elements_kind, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS))) {
2929  IF (__ Word32Equal(elements_kind, HOLEY_ELEMENTS)) {
2930  V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
2931  array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
2932  // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
2933  __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2934  elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(HOLEY_ELEMENTS),
2935  index, AllocateHeapNumber(value));
2936  GOTO(done);
2937  }
2938 
2939  __ Unreachable();
2940  }
2941  }
2942 
2943  V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
2944  array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
2945  __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2946  elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), index,
2947  __ Float64SilenceNaN(value));
2948  GOTO(done);
2949 
2950  BIND(done);
2951  break;
2952  }
2953  case TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kOddballElement:
2954  case TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kNonNumberElement: {
2955  // Possibly transition array based on input and store.
2956  //
2957  // -- TRANSITION PHASE -----------------
2958  // kind = ElementsKind(array)
2959  // if kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS {
2960  // Transition array to HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2961  // } else if kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
2962  // Transition array to HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2963  // }
2964  //
2965  // -- STORE PHASE ----------------------
2966  // // kind is HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2967  // Store array[index] = value
2968  //
2969  IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, elements_kind))) {
2970  // Transition {array} from HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS to HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
2971  TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS,
2972  fast_map.ToHandleChecked());
2973  } ELSE IF (UNLIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_ELEMENTS, elements_kind))) {
2974  TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS,
2975  fast_map.ToHandleChecked());
2976  }
2977 
2978  V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
2979  array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
2980  ElementAccess access =
2981  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
2982  if (kind == TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kOddballElement) {
2983  access.type = compiler::Type::BooleanOrNullOrUndefined();
2984  access.write_barrier_kind = kNoWriteBarrier;
2985  }
2986  __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(elements, access, index, value);
2987  break;
2988  }
2989  case TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kSignedSmallElement: {
2990  // Store a signed small in an output array.
2991  //
2992  // kind = ElementsKind(array)
2993  //
2994  // -- STORE PHASE ----------------------
2995  // if kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
2996  // float_value = convert int32 to float
2997  // Store array[index] = float_value
2998  // } else {
2999  // // kind is HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS
3000  // smi_value = convert int32 to smi
3001  // Store array[index] = smi_value
3002  // }
3003  //
3004  V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
3005  array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
3006  IF (__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_ELEMENTS, elements_kind)) {
3007  // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
3008  V<Float64> f64 = __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(value);
3009  __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
3010  elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), index,
3011  f64);
3012  } ELSE {
3013  // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
3014  // In this case, we know our value is a signed small, and we can
3015  // optimize the ElementAccess information.
3016  ElementAccess access = AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement();
3017  access.type = compiler::Type::SignedSmall();
3018  access.machine_type = MachineType::TaggedSigned();
3019  access.write_barrier_kind = kNoWriteBarrier;
3020  __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(elements, access, index,
3021  __ TagSmi(value));
3022  }
3023 
3024  break;
3025  }
3026  }
3027 
3028  return V<None>::Invalid();
3029  }

3031  V<Word32> REDUCE(CompareMaps)(V<HeapObject> heap_object, OptionalV<Map> map,
3032  const ZoneRefSet<Map>& maps) {
3033  if (!map.has_value()) {
3034  map = __ LoadMapField(heap_object);
3035  }
3036  return CompareMapAgainstMultipleMaps(map.value(), maps);
3037  }
3038 
3039  V<None> REDUCE(CheckMaps)(V<HeapObject> heap_object,
3040  V<FrameState> frame_state, OptionalV<Map> map,
3041  const ZoneRefSet<Map>& maps, CheckMapsFlags flags,
3042  const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
3043  if (maps.is_empty()) {
3044  __ Deoptimize(frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, feedback);
3045  return {};
3046  }
3047 
3048  V<Map> heap_object_map;
3049  if (map.has_value()) {
3050  heap_object_map = map.value();
3051  } else {
3052  heap_object_map = __ LoadMapField(heap_object);
3053  }
3054 
3055  if (flags & CheckMapsFlag::kTryMigrateInstance) {
3056  IF_NOT (LIKELY(CompareMapAgainstMultipleMaps(heap_object_map, maps))) {
3057  // Reloading the map slightly reduces register pressure, and we are on a
3058  // slow path here anyway.
3059  MigrateInstanceOrDeopt(heap_object, heap_object_map, frame_state,
3060  feedback);
3061  heap_object_map = __ LoadMapField(heap_object);
3062  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ CompareMaps(heap_object, heap_object_map, maps),
3063  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, feedback);
3064  }
3065  } else if (flags & CheckMapsFlag::kTryMigrateInstanceAndDeopt) {
3066  IF_NOT (LIKELY(CompareMapAgainstMultipleMaps(heap_object_map, maps))) {
3067  TryMigrateInstanceAndMarkMapAsMigrationTarget(
3068  heap_object, heap_object_map, frame_state, feedback);
3069  __ Deoptimize(frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, feedback);
3070  }
3071  } else {
3072  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ CompareMaps(heap_object, heap_object_map, maps),
3073  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, feedback);
3074  }
3075  // Inserting a AssumeMap so that subsequent optimizations know the map of
3076  // this object.
3077  __ AssumeMap(heap_object, maps);
3078  return {};
3079  }

3081  V<Float> REDUCE(FloatUnary)(V<Float> input, FloatUnaryOp::Kind kind,
3082  FloatRepresentation rep) {
3083  LABEL_BLOCK(no_change) { return Next::ReduceFloatUnary(input, kind, rep); }
3084  switch (kind) {
3085  case FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundUp:
3086  case FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundDown:
3087  case FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundTiesEven:
3088  case FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundToZero: {
3089  // TODO(14108): Implement for Float32.
3090  if (rep == FloatRepresentation::Float32()) {
3091  goto no_change;
3092  }
3093  DCHECK_EQ(rep, FloatRepresentation::Float64());
3094  V<Float64> input_f64 = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
3095  if (FloatUnaryOp::IsSupported(kind, rep)) {
3096  // If we have a fast machine operation for this, we can just keep it.
3097  goto no_change;
3098  }
3099  // Otherwise we have to lower it.
3100  V<Float64> two_52 = __ Float64Constant(4503599627370496.0E0);
3101  V<Float64> minus_two_52 = __ Float64Constant(-4503599627370496.0E0);
3102 
3103  if (kind == FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundUp) {
3104  // General case for ceil.
3105  //
3106  // if 0.0 < input then
3107  // if 2^52 <= input then
3108  // input
3109  // else
3110  // let temp1 = (2^52 + input) - 2^52 in
3111  // if temp1 < input then
3112  // temp1 + 1
3113  // else
3114  // temp1
3115  // else
3116  // if input == 0 then
3117  // input
3118  // else
3119  // if input <= -2^52 then
3120  // input
3121  // else
3122  // let temp1 = -0 - input in
3123  // let temp2 = (2^52 + temp1) - 2^52 in
3124  // if temp1 < temp2 then -0 - (temp2 - 1) else -0 - temp2
3125 
3126  Label<Float64> done(this);
3127 
3128  IF (LIKELY(__ Float64LessThan(0.0, input_f64))) {
3129  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Float64LessThanOrEqual(two_52, input_f64)),
3130  done, input_f64);
3131  V<Float64> temp1 =
3132  __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, input_f64), two_52);
3133  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64LessThan(temp1, input_f64), done, temp1);
3134  GOTO(done, __ Float64Add(temp1, 1.0));
3135  } ELSE IF (UNLIKELY(__ Float64Equal(input_f64, 0.0))) {
3136  GOTO(done, input_f64);
3137  } ELSE IF (UNLIKELY(
3138  __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(input_f64, minus_two_52))) {
3139  GOTO(done, input_f64);
3140  } ELSE {
3141  V<Float64> temp1 = __ Float64Sub(-0.0, input_f64);
3142  V<Float64> temp2 =
3143  __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, temp1), two_52);
3144  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64LessThan(temp1, temp2), done,
3145  __ Float64Sub(-0.0, temp2));
3146  GOTO(done, __ Float64Sub(-0.0, __ Float64Sub(temp2, 1.0)));
3147  }
3148 
3149  BIND(done, result);
3150  return result;
3151  } else if (kind == FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundDown) {
3152  // General case for floor.
3153  //
3154  // if 0.0 < input then
3155  // if 2^52 <= input then
3156  // input
3157  // else
3158  // let temp1 = (2^52 + input) - 2^52 in
3159  // if input < temp1 then
3160  // temp1 - 1
3161  // else
3162  // temp1
3163  // else
3164  // if input == 0 then
3165  // input
3166  // else
3167  // if input <= -2^52 then
3168  // input
3169  // else
3170  // let temp1 = -0 - input in
3171  // let temp2 = (2^52 + temp1) - 2^52 in
3172  // if temp2 < temp1 then
3173  // -1 - temp2
3174  // else
3175  // -0 - temp2
3176 
3177  Label<Float64> done(this);
3178 
3179  IF (LIKELY(__ Float64LessThan(0.0, input_f64))) {
3180  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Float64LessThanOrEqual(two_52, input_f64)),
3181  done, input_f64);
3182  V<Float64> temp1 =
3183  __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, input_f64), two_52);
3184  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64LessThan(input_f64, temp1), done, temp1);
3185  GOTO(done, __ Float64Sub(temp1, 1.0));
3186  } ELSE IF (UNLIKELY(__ Float64Equal(input_f64, 0.0))) {
3187  GOTO(done, input_f64);
3188  } ELSE IF (UNLIKELY(
3189  __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(input_f64, minus_two_52))) {
3190  GOTO(done, input_f64);
3191  } ELSE {
3192  V<Float64> temp1 = __ Float64Sub(-0.0, input_f64);
3193  V<Float64> temp2 =
3194  __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, temp1), two_52);
3195  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64LessThan(temp2, temp1), done,
3196  __ Float64Sub(-0.0, temp2));
3197  GOTO(done, __ Float64Sub(-1.0, temp2));
3198  }
3199 
3200  BIND(done, result);
3201  return result;
3202  } else if (kind == FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundTiesEven) {
3203  // Generate case for round ties to even:
3204  //
3205  // let value = floor(input) in
3206  // let temp1 = input - value in
3207  // if temp1 < 0.5 then
3208  // value
3209  // else if 0.5 < temp1 then
3210  // value + 1.0
3211  // else
3212  // let temp2 = value % 2.0 in
3213  // if temp2 == 0.0 then
3214  // value
3215  // else
3216  // value + 1.0
3217 
3218  Label<Float64> done(this);
3219 
3220  V<Float64> value = __ Float64RoundDown(input_f64);
3221  V<Float64> temp1 = __ Float64Sub(input_f64, value);
3222  GOTO_IF(__ Float64LessThan(temp1, 0.5), done, value);
3223  GOTO_IF(__ Float64LessThan(0.5, temp1), done,
3224  __ Float64Add(value, 1.0));
3225 
3226  V<Float64> temp2 = __ Float64Mod(value, 2.0);
3227  GOTO_IF(__ Float64Equal(temp2, 0.0), done, value);
3228  GOTO(done, __ Float64Add(value, 1.0));
3229 
3230  BIND(done, result);
3231  return result;
3232  } else if (kind == FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundToZero) {
3233  // General case for trunc.
3234  //
3235  // if 0.0 < input then
3236  // if 2^52 <= input then
3237  // input
3238  // else
3239  // let temp1 = (2^52 + input) - 2^52 in
3240  // if input < temp1 then
3241  // temp1 - 1
3242  // else
3243  // temp1
3244  // else
3245  // if input == 0 then
3246  // input
3247  // if input <= -2^52 then
3248  // input
3249  // else
3250  // let temp1 = -0 - input in
3251  // let temp2 = (2^52 + temp1) - 2^52 in
3252  // if temp1 < temp2 then
3253  // -0 - (temp2 - 1)
3254  // else
3255  // -0 - temp2
3256 
3257  Label<Float64> done(this);
3258 
3259  IF (__ Float64LessThan(0.0, input_f64)) {
3260  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Float64LessThanOrEqual(two_52, input_f64)),
3261  done, input_f64);
3262 
3263  V<Float64> temp1 =
3264  __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, input_f64), two_52);
3265  GOTO_IF(__ Float64LessThan(input_f64, temp1), done,
3266  __ Float64Sub(temp1, 1.0));
3267  GOTO(done, temp1);
3268  } ELSE {
3269  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Float64Equal(input_f64, 0.0)), done, input_f64);
3270  GOTO_IF(
3271  UNLIKELY(__ Float64LessThanOrEqual(input_f64, minus_two_52)),
3272  done, input_f64);
3273 
3274  V<Float64> temp1 = __ Float64Sub(-0.0, input_f64);
3275  V<Float64> temp2 =
3276  __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, temp1), two_52);
3277 
3278  IF (__ Float64LessThan(temp1, temp2)) {
3279  GOTO(done, __ Float64Sub(-0.0, __ Float64Sub(temp2, 1.0)));
3280  } ELSE {
3281  GOTO(done, __ Float64Sub(-0.0, temp2));
3282  }
3283  }
3284 
3285  BIND(done, result);
3286  return result;
3287  }
3288  UNREACHABLE();
3289  }
3290  default:
3291  DCHECK(FloatUnaryOp::IsSupported(kind, rep));
3292  goto no_change;
3293  }
3294  UNREACHABLE();
3295  }

3297  V<Object> REDUCE(CheckedClosure)(V<Object> input, V<FrameState> frame_state,

3318  V<None> REDUCE(CheckEqualsInternalizedString)(V<Object> expected,
3319  V<Object> value,
3320  V<FrameState> frame_state) {
3321  Label<> done(this);
3322  // Check if {expected} and {value} are the same, which is the likely case.
3323  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(expected, value)), done);
3324 
3325  // Now {value} could still be a non-internalized String that matches
3326  // {expected}.
3327  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ ObjectIsSmi(value), frame_state,
3328  DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName, FeedbackSource{});
3329  V<Map> value_map = __ LoadMapField(value);
3330  V<Word32> value_instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(value_map);
3331  V<Word32> value_representation =
3332  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(value_instance_type, kStringRepresentationMask);
3333  // ThinString
3334  IF (__ Word32Equal(value_representation, kThinStringTag)) {
3335  // The {value} is a ThinString, let's check the actual value.
3336  V<String> value_actual = __ template LoadField<String>(
3337  value, AccessBuilder::ForThinStringActual());
3338  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ TaggedEqual(expected, value_actual), frame_state,
3339  DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName, FeedbackSource{});
3340  } ELSE {
3341  // Check that the {value} is a non-internalized String, if it's anything
3342  // else it cannot match the recorded feedback {expected} anyways.
3343  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
3344  __ Word32Equal(
3345  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(value_instance_type,
3346  kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask),
3347  kStringTag | kNotInternalizedTag),
3348  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName, FeedbackSource{});
3349 
3350  // Try to find the {value} in the string table.
3351  MachineSignature::Builder builder(__ graph_zone(), 1, 2);
3352  builder.AddReturn(MachineType::AnyTagged());
3353  builder.AddParam(MachineType::Pointer());
3354  builder.AddParam(MachineType::AnyTagged());
3355  OpIndex try_string_to_index_or_lookup_existing = __ ExternalConstant(
3356  ExternalReference::try_string_to_index_or_lookup_existing());
3357  OpIndex isolate_ptr =
3358  __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::isolate_address());
3359  V<String> value_internalized = V<String>::Cast(__ Call(
3360  try_string_to_index_or_lookup_existing, {isolate_ptr, value},
3361  TSCallDescriptor::Create(
3362  Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(__ graph_zone(), builder.Get()),
3363  CanThrow::kNo, LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo, __ graph_zone())));
3364 
3365  // Now see if the results match.
3366  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ TaggedEqual(expected, value_internalized),
3367  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName,
3368  FeedbackSource{});
3369  }
3370 
3371  GOTO(done);
3372 
3373  BIND(done);
3374  return V<None>::Invalid();
3375  }

3398  V<Word32> REDUCE(Float64SameValue)(V<Float64> left, V<Float64> right) {
3399  Label<Word32> done(this);
3400 
3401  // TODO(dmercadier): Optimize if one of the sides is a constant.
3402  IF (__ Float64Equal(left, right)) {
3403  // Even if the values are float64-equal, we still need to distinguish
3404  // zero and minus zero.
3405  V<Word32> left_hi = __ Float64ExtractHighWord32(left);
3406  V<Word32> right_hi = __ Float64ExtractHighWord32(right);
3407  GOTO(done, __ Word32Equal(left_hi, right_hi));
3408  } ELSE {
3409  // Return true iff both {lhs} and {rhs} are NaN.
3410  GOTO_IF(__ Float64Equal(left, left), done, 0);
3411  GOTO_IF(__ Float64Equal(right, right), done, 0);
3412  GOTO(done, 1);
3413  }
3414 
3415  BIND(done, result);
3416  return result;
3417  }

3446  V<Object> REDUCE(MaybeGrowFastElements)(V<Object> object, V<Object> elements,
3447  V<Word32> index,
3448  V<Word32> elements_length,
3449  V<FrameState> frame_state,
3450  GrowFastElementsMode mode,
3451  const FeedbackSource& feedback) {

3453  // Check if we need to grow the {elements} backing store.
3454  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ Uint32LessThan(index, elements_length)), done, elements);
3455  // We need to grow the {elements} for {object}.
3456  V<Object> new_elements;

3464  isolate_, object, __ TagSmi(index));
3465  break;
3466  }
3467

3469  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ ObjectIsSmi(new_elements), frame_state,
3470  DeoptimizeReason::kCouldNotGrowElements, feedback);

3477  V<None> REDUCE(TransitionElementsKind)(V<HeapObject> object,
3478  const ElementsTransition& transition) {
3479  V<Map> source_map = __ HeapConstant(transition.source().object());
3480  V<Map> target_map = __ HeapConstant(transition.target().object());
3481 
3482  // Load the current map of {object}.
3483  V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
3484 
3485  // Check if {map} is the same as {source_map}.
3486  IF (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(map, source_map))) {
3487  switch (transition.mode()) {
3488  case ElementsTransition::kFastTransition:
3489  // In-place migration of {object}, just store the {target_map}.
3490  __ StoreField(object, AccessBuilder::ForMap(), target_map);
3491  break;
3492  case ElementsTransition::kSlowTransition:
3493  // Instance migration, call out to the runtime for {object}.
3494  __ CallRuntime_TransitionElementsKind(
3495  isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), object, target_map);
3496  break;
3497  }
3498  }
3499 
3500  return V<None>::Invalid();
3501  }
3502 
3503  V<None> REDUCE(TransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap)(
3504  V<HeapObject> object, V<Map> map, V<FrameState> frame_state,
3505  const ElementsTransitionWithMultipleSources& transition) {
3506  Label<> done(this);
3507 
3508  const MapRef target = transition.target();
3509  V<Map> target_map = __ HeapConstant(target.object());
3510 
3511  IF (LIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(map, target_map))) {
3512  GOTO(done);
3513  }
3514 
3515  const ZoneRefSet<Map>& transition_sources = transition.sources();
3516  for (const MapRef transition_source : transition_sources) {
3517  bool is_simple = IsSimpleMapChangeTransition(
3518  transition_source.elements_kind(), target.elements_kind());
3519 
3520  IF (__ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(transition_source.object()))) {
3521  if (is_simple) {
3522  // In-place migration of {object}, just store the {target_map}.
3523  __ StoreField(object, AccessBuilder::ForMap(), target_map);
3524  } else {
3525  // Instance migration, call out to the runtime for {object}.
3526  __ CallRuntime_TransitionElementsKind(
3527  isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), object, target_map);
3528  }
3529  GOTO(done);
3530  }
3531  }
3532  // Successful transitions jumped to `done`. If we didn't jump, we know the
3533  // map is not the target map.
3534  __ Deoptimize(frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap,
3535  transition.feedback());
3536 
3537  BIND(done);
3538 
3539  // Inserting a AssumeMap so that subsequent optimizations know the map of
3540  // this object.
3541  ZoneRefSet<Map> maps({target}, __ graph_zone());
3542  __ AssumeMap(object, maps);
3543 
3544  return V<None>::Invalid();
3545  }

3547  OpIndex REDUCE(FindOrderedHashEntry)(V<Object> data_structure, OpIndex key,
3548  FindOrderedHashEntryOp::Kind kind) {
3549  switch (kind) {
3550  case FindOrderedHashEntryOp::Kind::kFindOrderedHashMapEntry:
3551  return __ CallBuiltin_FindOrderedHashMapEntry(
3552  isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), data_structure, key);
3553  case FindOrderedHashEntryOp::Kind::kFindOrderedHashMapEntryForInt32Key: {
3554  // Compute the integer hash code.
3555  V<WordPtr> hash = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(ComputeUnseededHash(key));
3556 
3557  V<WordPtr> number_of_buckets =
3558  __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(__ template LoadField<Smi>(
3559  data_structure,
3560  AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfBuckets())));
3561  hash = __ WordPtrBitwiseAnd(hash, __ WordPtrSub(number_of_buckets, 1));
3562  V<WordPtr> first_entry = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(__ Load(
3563  data_structure,
3564  __ WordPtrAdd(__ WordPtrShiftLeft(hash, kTaggedSizeLog2),
3565  OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartOffset()),
3566  LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(), MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned())));
3567 
3568  Label<WordPtr> done(this);
3569  LoopLabel<WordPtr> loop(this);
3570  GOTO(loop, first_entry);
3571 
3572  BIND_LOOP(loop, entry) {
3573  GOTO_IF(__ WordPtrEqual(entry, OrderedHashMap::kNotFound), done,
3574  entry);
3575  V<WordPtr> candidate =
3576  __ WordPtrAdd(__ WordPtrMul(entry, OrderedHashMap::kEntrySize),
3577  number_of_buckets);
3578  V<Object> candidate_key = __ Load(
3579  data_structure,
3580  __ WordPtrAdd(__ WordPtrShiftLeft(candidate, kTaggedSizeLog2),
3581  OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartOffset()),
3582  LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(), MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged());
3583 
3584  IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(candidate_key))) {
3585  GOTO_IF(
3586  __ Word32Equal(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(candidate_key)), key),
3587  done, candidate);
3588  } ELSE IF (__ TaggedEqual(
3589  __ LoadMapField(candidate_key),
3590  __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()))) {
3591  GOTO_IF(__ Float64Equal(__ LoadHeapNumberValue(
3592  V<HeapNumber>::Cast(candidate_key)),
3593  __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(key)),
3594  done, candidate);
3595  }
3596 
3597  V<WordPtr> next_entry = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(__ Load(
3598  data_structure,
3599  __ WordPtrAdd(__ WordPtrShiftLeft(candidate, kTaggedSizeLog2),
3600  (OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartOffset() +
3601  OrderedHashMap::kChainOffset * kTaggedSize)),
3602  LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
3603  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned())));
3604  GOTO(loop, next_entry);
3605  }
3606 
3607  BIND(done, result);
3608  return result;
3609  }
3610  case FindOrderedHashEntryOp::Kind::kFindOrderedHashSetEntry:
3611  return __ CallBuiltin_FindOrderedHashSetEntry(
3612  isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), data_structure, key);
3613  }
3614  }

3616  // Loads a surrogate pair from {string} starting at {index} and returns the
3617  // result encode in {encoding}. Note that UTF32 encoding is identical to the
3618  // code point. If the string's {length} is already available, it can be
3619  // passed, otherwise it will be loaded when required.
3620  V<Word32> LoadSurrogatePairAt(V<String> string, OptionalV<WordPtr> length,
3621  V<WordPtr> index, UnicodeEncoding encoding) {
3622  Label<Word32> done(this);
3623 
3624  V<Word32> first_code_unit = __ StringCharCodeAt(string, index);
3625  GOTO_IF_NOT(UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(
3626  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(first_code_unit, 0xFC00), 0xD800)),
3627  done, first_code_unit);
3628  if (!length.has_value()) {
3629  length = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(__ template LoadField<Word32>(
3630  string, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength()));
3631  }
3632  V<WordPtr> next_index = __ WordPtrAdd(index, 1);
3633  GOTO_IF_NOT(__ IntPtrLessThan(next_index, length.value()), done,
3634  first_code_unit);
3635 
3636  V<Word32> second_code_unit = __ StringCharCodeAt(string, next_index);
3637  GOTO_IF_NOT(
3638  __ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(second_code_unit, 0xFC00), 0xDC00),
3639  done, first_code_unit);
3640 
3641  switch (encoding) {
3642  case UnicodeEncoding::UTF16: {
3643 // Need to swap the order for big-endian platforms
3644 #if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
3645  V<Word32> value = __ Word32BitwiseOr(
3646  __ Word32ShiftLeft(first_code_unit, 16), second_code_unit);
3647 #else
3648  V<Word32> value = __ Word32BitwiseOr(
3649  __ Word32ShiftLeft(second_code_unit, 16), first_code_unit);
3650 #endif
3651  GOTO(done, value);
3652  break;
3653  }
3654  case UnicodeEncoding::UTF32: {
3655  const int32_t surrogate_offset = 0x10000 - (0xD800 << 10) - 0xDC00;
3656  V<Word32> value =
3657  __ Word32Add(__ Word32ShiftLeft(first_code_unit, 10),
3658  __ Word32Add(second_code_unit, surrogate_offset));
3659  GOTO(done, value);
3660  break;
3661  }
3662  }
3663 
3664  BIND(done, result);
3665  return result;
3666  }
3667 
3668  V<String> StringFromSingleCharCode(V<Word32> code) {
3669  Label<String> done(this);
3670 
3671  // Check if the {code} is a one byte character.
3672  IF (LIKELY(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(code, String::kMaxOneByteCharCode))) {
3673  // Load the string for the {code} directly from the roots table.
3674  V<WordPtr> index = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(code);
3675  V<String> entry = __ LoadOffHeap(
3676  __ LoadRootRegister(), index,
3677  IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kFirstSingleCharacterString),
3678  MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer());
3679 
3680  // Use the {entry} from the {table}.
3681  GOTO(done, entry);
3682  } ELSE {
3683  Uninitialized<SeqTwoByteString> string =
3684  AllocateSeqTwoByteString(1, AllocationType::kYoung);
3685  __ InitializeElement(
3686  string, AccessBuilderTS::ForSeqTwoByteStringCharacter(), 0, code);
3687  GOTO(done, __ FinishInitialization(std::move(string)));
3688  }
3689 
3690  BIND(done, result);
3691  return result;
3692  }
3693 
3694  V<String> StringFromSingleCodePoint(V<Word32> codepoint,
3695  UnicodeEncoding encoding) {
3696  Label<String> done(this);
3697  // Check if the input is a single code unit.
3698  GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ Uint32LessThan(codepoint, 0x10000)), done,
3699  StringFromSingleCharCode(codepoint));
3700 
3701  V<Word32> code;
3702  switch (encoding) {
3703  case UnicodeEncoding::UTF16:
3704  code = codepoint;
3705  break;
3706  case UnicodeEncoding::UTF32: {
3707  // Convert UTF32 to UTF16 code units and store as a 32 bit word.
3708  V<Word32> lead_offset = __ Word32Constant(0xD800 - (0x10000 >> 10));
3709 
3710  // lead = (codepoint >> 10) + LEAD_OFFSET
3711  V<Word32> lead = __ Word32Add(__ Word32ShiftRightLogical(codepoint, 10),
3712  lead_offset);
3713 
3714  // trail = (codepoint & 0x3FF) + 0xDC00
3715  V<Word32> trail =
3716  __ Word32Add(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(codepoint, 0x3FF), 0xDC00);
3717 
3718  // codepoint = (trail << 16) | lead
3719 #if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
3720  code = __ Word32BitwiseOr(__ Word32ShiftLeft(lead, 16), trail);
3721 #else
3722  code = __ Word32BitwiseOr(__ Word32ShiftLeft(trail, 16), lead);
3723 #endif
3724  break;
3725  }
3726  }
3727 
3728  Uninitialized<SeqTwoByteString> string =
3729  AllocateSeqTwoByteString(2, AllocationType::kYoung);
3730  // Write the code as a single 32-bit value by adapting the elements
3731  // access to SeqTwoByteString characters.
3732  auto access = AccessBuilderTS::ForSeqTwoByteStringCharacter();
3733  access.machine_type = MachineType::Uint32();
3734  __ InitializeElement(string, access, 0, code);
3735  GOTO(done, __ FinishInitialization(std::move(string)));
3736 
3737  BIND(done, result);
3738  return result;
3739  }
3740 
3741  Uninitialized<SeqTwoByteString> AllocateSeqTwoByteString(
3742  uint32_t length, AllocationType type) {
3743  __ CodeComment("AllocateSeqTwoByteString");
3744  DCHECK_GT(length, 0);
3745  // Allocate a new string object.
3746  Uninitialized<SeqTwoByteString> string =
3747  __ template Allocate<SeqTwoByteString>(
3748  SeqTwoByteString::SizeFor(length), type, kTaggedAligned);
3749  // Set padding to 0.
3750  __ Initialize(string, __ IntPtrConstant(0),
3751  MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned(),
3752  WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier,
3753  SeqTwoByteString::SizeFor(length) - kObjectAlignment);
3754  // Initialize remaining fields.
3755  __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilderTS::ForMap(),
3756  __ SeqTwoByteStringMapConstant());
3757  __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilderTS::ForStringLength(), length);
3758  __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilderTS::ForNameRawHashField(),
3759  Name::kEmptyHashField);
3760  // Do not finish allocation here, because the caller has to initialize
3761  // characters.
3762  return string;
3763  }

3780  private:
3781  V<Word32> BuildUint32Mod(V<Word32> left, V<Word32> right) {
3782  Label<Word32> done(this);
3783 
3784  // Compute the mask for the {rhs}.
3785  V<Word32> msk = __ Word32Sub(right, 1);
3786 
3787  // Check if the {rhs} is a power of two.
3788  IF (__ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(right, msk), 0)) {
3789  // The {rhs} is a power of two, just do a fast bit masking.
3790  GOTO(done, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(left, msk));
3791  } ELSE {
3792  // The {rhs} is not a power of two, do a generic Uint32Mod.
3793  GOTO(done, __ Uint32Mod(left, right));
3794  }
3795 
3796  BIND(done, result);
3797  return result;
3798  }

3800  // Pass {bitfield} = {digit} = OpIndex::Invalid() to construct the canonical
3801  // 0n BigInt.
3802  V<BigInt> AllocateBigInt(V<Word32> bitfield, V<Word64> digit) {
3803  if (Asm().generating_unreachable_operations()) return V<BigInt>::Invalid();
3804 
3805  DCHECK(Is64());
3806  DCHECK_EQ(bitfield.valid(), digit.valid());
3807  static constexpr auto zero_bitfield =
3808  BigInt::SignBits::update(BigInt::LengthBits::encode(0), false);
3809 
3810  V<Map> map = __ HeapConstant(factory_->bigint_map());
3811  auto bigint = __ template Allocate<FreshlyAllocatedBigInt>(
3812  __ IntPtrConstant(BigInt::SizeFor(digit.valid() ? 1 : 0)),
3813  AllocationType::kYoung, kTaggedAligned);
3814  __ InitializeField(bigint, AccessBuilder::ForMap(), map);
3815  __ InitializeField(
3816  bigint, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntBitfield(),
3817  bitfield.valid() ? bitfield : __ Word32Constant(zero_bitfield));
3818 
3819  // BigInts have no padding on 64 bit architectures with pointer compression.
3820 #ifdef BIGINT_NEEDS_PADDING
3821  __ InitializeField(bigint, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntOptionalPadding(),
3822  __ Word32Constant(0));
3823 #endif
3824  if (digit.valid()) {
3825  __ InitializeField(
3826  bigint, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntLeastSignificantDigit64(), digit);
3827  }
3828  return V<BigInt>::Cast(__ FinishInitialization(std::move(bigint)));
3829  }

3831  void TagSmiOrOverflow(V<Word32> input, Label<>* overflow,
3832  Label<Number>* done) {
3833  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
3834 
3835  // Check for overflow at the same time that we are smi tagging.
3836  // Since smi tagging shifts left by one, it's the same as adding value
3837  // twice.
3838  V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> add = __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(input, input);
3839  V<Word32> check = __ template Projection<1>(add);
3840  GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(check), *overflow);
3841  GOTO(*done, __ BitcastWord32ToSmi(__ template Projection<0>(add)));
3842  }

3846  return __ Word32Equal(__ Word32Equal(value, 0), 0);

3853  V<Float64> ConvertHeapObjectToFloat64OrDeopt(
3854  V<Object> heap_object, V<FrameState> frame_state,
3855  ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind input_kind,
3856  const FeedbackSource& feedback,
3857  OptionalV<Map> loaded_map = OptionalV<Map>::Nullopt()) {
3858  V<Map> map = loaded_map.value_or_invalid();
3859  if (!map.valid()) map = __ LoadMapField(heap_object);
3860  switch (input_kind) {
3861  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi:
3862  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
3863  kNumberOrString:
3864  UNREACHABLE();
3865  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
3866  kAdditiveSafeInteger: {
3867  V<Word32> is_number =
3868  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()));
3869  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(is_number, frame_state,
3870  DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber, feedback);
3871  __ ChangeFloat64ToAdditiveSafeIntegerOrDeopt(
3872  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(heap_object)),
3873  frame_state, CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero, feedback);
3874  break;
3875  }
3876  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber: {
3877  V<Word32> is_number =
3878  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()));
3879  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(is_number, frame_state,
3880  DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber, feedback);
3881  break;
3882  }
3883  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
3884  kNumberOrBoolean: {
3885 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
3886  // TODO(leszeks): Consider checking the boolean oddballs by value,
3887  // before loading the map.
3888  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap + Map::kSize ==
3889  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kHeapNumberMap);
3890  V<Word32> map_int32 =
3891  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map));
3892  V<Word32> is_in_range = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
3893  __ Word32Sub(map_int32,
3894  __ Word32Constant(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap)),
3895  __ Word32Constant(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kHeapNumberMap -
3896  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap));
3897  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(is_in_range, frame_state,
3898  DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumberOrBoolean, feedback);
3899 #else
3900  IF_NOT (__ TaggedEqual(map,
3901  __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()))) {
3902  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
3903  __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->boolean_map())),
3904  frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumberOrBoolean, feedback);
3905  }
3906 #endif
3907 
3908  break;
3909  }
3910  case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
3911  kNumberOrOddball: {
3912 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
3913  constexpr auto kNumberOrOddballRange =
3914  InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange(
3915  HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE, ODDBALL_TYPE)
3916  .value();
3917  V<Word32> map_int32 =
3918  __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map));
3919  V<Word32> is_in_range = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
3920  __ Word32Sub(map_int32,
3921  __ Word32Constant(kNumberOrOddballRange.first)),
3922  __ Word32Constant(kNumberOrOddballRange.second -
3923  kNumberOrOddballRange.first));
3924  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(is_in_range, frame_state,
3925  DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumberOrOddball, feedback);
3926 #else
3927  IF_NOT (__ TaggedEqual(map,
3928  __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()))) {
3929  // For oddballs also contain the numeric value, let us just check that
3930  // we have an oddball here.
3931  V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
3932  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ Word32Equal(instance_type, ODDBALL_TYPE),
3933  frame_state,
3934  DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumberOrOddball, feedback);
3935  }
3936 #endif
3937 
3938  break;
3939  }
3940  }
3941  return __ template LoadField<Float64>(
3942  heap_object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
3943  }

3945  V<Word32> LoadFromSeqString(V<Object> receiver, V<WordPtr> position,
3946  V<Word32> onebyte) {
3947  Label<Word32> done(this);
3948 
3949  IF (onebyte) {
3950  GOTO(done, __ template LoadNonArrayBufferElement<Word32>(
3951  receiver, AccessBuilder::ForSeqOneByteStringCharacter(),
3952  position));
3953  } ELSE {
3954  GOTO(done, __ template LoadNonArrayBufferElement<Word32>(
3955  receiver, AccessBuilder::ForSeqTwoByteStringCharacter(),
3956  position));
3957  }
3958 
3959  BIND(done, result);
3960  return result;
3961  }

3963  void MigrateInstanceOrDeopt(V<HeapObject> heap_object, V<Map> heap_object_map,
3964  V<FrameState> frame_state,
3965  const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
3966  // If {heap_object_map} is not deprecated, the migration attempt does not
3967  // make sense.
3968  V<Word32> bitfield3 = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
3969  heap_object_map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField3());
3970  V<Word32> deprecated =
3971  __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield3, Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit::kMask);
3972  __ DeoptimizeIfNot(deprecated, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap,
3973  feedback);
3974  V<Object> result = __ CallRuntime_TryMigrateInstance(
3975  isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), heap_object);
3976  // TryMigrateInstance returns a Smi value to signal failure.
3977  __ DeoptimizeIf(__ ObjectIsSmi(result), frame_state,
3978  DeoptimizeReason::kInstanceMigrationFailed, feedback);
3979  }

3996  // TODO(nicohartmann@): Might use the CallBuiltinDescriptors here.
3997  OpIndex CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(Builtin builtin,
3998  std::initializer_list<OpIndex> arguments) {
3999  DCHECK_IMPLIES(builtin == Builtin::kBigIntUnaryMinus,
4000  arguments.size() == 1);
4001  DCHECK_IMPLIES(builtin != Builtin::kBigIntUnaryMinus,
4002  arguments.size() == 2);
4003  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 4> args(arguments);
4004  args.push_back(__ NoContextConstant());
4005 
4006  Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate_, builtin);
4007  auto descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
4008  __ graph_zone(), callable.descriptor(),
4009  callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
4010  CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kFoldable | Operator::kNoThrow);
4011  auto ts_descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
4012  descriptor, CanThrow::kNo, LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo, __ graph_zone());
4013  return __ Call(__ HeapConstant(callable.code()), V<FrameState>::Invalid(),
4014  base::VectorOf(args), ts_descriptor);
4015  }

4033  case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseXor:

4042  V<WordPtr> BuildTypedArrayDataPointer(V<Object> base, V<WordPtr> external) {
4043  if (__ matcher().MatchZero(base)) return external;
4044  V<WordPtr> untagged_base = __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(base);
4045  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
4046  // Zero-extend Tagged_t to UintPtr according to current compression
4047  // scheme so that the addition with |external_pointer| (which already
4048  // contains compensated offset value) will decompress the tagged value.
4049  // See JSTypedArray::ExternalPointerCompensationForOnHeapArray() for
4050  // details.
4051  untagged_base =
4052  __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(untagged_base));
4053  }
4054  return __ WordPtrAdd(untagged_base, external);
4055  }

4057  V<Word32> ComputeUnseededHash(V<Word32> value) {
4058  // See v8::internal::ComputeUnseededHash()
4059  value = __ Word32Add(__ Word32BitwiseXor(value, 0xFFFFFFFF),
4060  __ Word32ShiftLeft(value, 15));
4061  value = __ Word32BitwiseXor(value, __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(value, 12));
4062  value = __ Word32Add(value, __ Word32ShiftLeft(value, 2));
4063  value = __ Word32BitwiseXor(value, __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(value, 4));
4064  value = __ Word32Mul(value, 2057);
4065  value = __ Word32BitwiseXor(value, __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(value, 16));
4066  value = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(value, 0x3FFFFFFF);
4067  return value;
4068  }

4070  void TransitionElementsTo(V<JSArray> array, ElementsKind from,
4071  ElementsKind to, Handle<Map> target_map) {
4072  DCHECK(IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(from, to));
4073  DCHECK(to == HOLEY_ELEMENTS || to == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
4074 
4075  if (IsSimpleMapChangeTransition(from, to)) {
4076  __ StoreField(array, AccessBuilder::ForMap(),
4077  __ HeapConstant(target_map));
4078  } else {
4079  // Instance migration, call out to the runtime for {array}.
4080  __ CallRuntime_TransitionElementsKind(isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(),
4081  array, __ HeapConstant(target_map));
4082  }
4083  }

4085  V<Word32> CompareMapAgainstMultipleMaps(V<Map> heap_object_map,
4086  const ZoneRefSet<Map>& maps) {
4087  if (maps.is_empty()) {
4088  return __ Word32Constant(0);
4089  }
4090  V<Word32> result;
4091  for (size_t i = 0; i < maps.size(); ++i) {
4092  V<Map> map = __ HeapConstant(maps[i].object());
4093  if (i == 0) {
4094  result = __ TaggedEqual(heap_object_map, map);
4095  } else {
4096  result =
4097  __ Word32BitwiseOr(result, __ TaggedEqual(heap_object_map, map));
4098  }
4099  }
4100  return result;
4101  }

4103  bool DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector() {
4104  if (!undetectable_objects_protector_) {
4105  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded unpark(broker_);
4106  undetectable_objects_protector_ =
4107  broker_->dependencies()->DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector();
4108  }
4109  return *undetectable_objects_protector_;
4110  }
4111 
4112  Isolate* isolate_ = __ data() -> isolate();
4113  Factory* factory_ = isolate_ ? isolate_->factory() : nullptr;
4114  JSHeapBroker* broker_ = __ data() -> broker();
4115  std::optional<bool> undetectable_objects_protector_ = {};
4116 };
